Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the second session then! Now it is time for the Indian openers, Rohit Sharma and Shubman Gill, as they make their way out. Following them to the middle are the Australian players. Mitchell Starc will get us underway with the ball. If he gets his radar right, India can be in trouble. Here he comes, with the first delivery...
... Day 2, Session 2...

Before that, hear what the legendary Allan Border has to say. Allan Border reckons that the average first innings score at Gabba is actually 330 and that Australia's score of 370 is actually very comprehensive. Adds further that the first hour of play, as far as India's batting is concerned, will be crucial. States that Starc can get the ball swinging. Says the ball did swing in the first session and sees no reason why Mitchell cannot do so. Feels the home side needs to strike early and that if they do, then that 370 total can look very good. Lavishes praise on Shubman and says that he is a good puller of the ball, but also adds that Gill has a long way to go and a lot to learn. Allan though feels that overall Shubman Gill is a wonder kid. On the weather, Border says that it is blue skies right now but says that thunderstorms are expected later on. Feels though that there may not be any disturbances to the second session and that effects of the thunderstorms, if any, might be felt only in the last session.

Right, so the players have broken for Lunch now. And when they come back, with India set to bat in their first innings, they have a task. Glenn McGrath and Sanjay Manjrekar (on air) reckon that it is a par total, even though the Aussies have not been able to get to 400. And expect their bowlers to come out hard at the visitors. The Indian openers need to get off to a good start. Well, join us shortly for the second session and for India's innings...

Yes, the Indians needed to be, and they were. They have contained the damage and although this may still be a big total, for a naive bowling attack, they deserve credit for suppressing the Australians well. The rookie debutants from Tamil Nadu, T Natarajan and Washington Sundar, netted 3 each. So did Shardul Thakur, although he strayed on the expensive side. Siraj got one, that of Warner, at the very start.

Earlier, after winning the toss, Australia opted to bat first. They lost their openers cheaply but the usual suspects, Smith and Labuschagne, stitched a revival stand. Smith eventually fell but there was a bigger stand shared between Labuschagne and Wade. The former later on went onto get his 5th Test ton as well. After that Paine and Green batted well too but they, combined with the tail, could not get their side to the 400-run mark, as India were exceptional at the start of Day 2.

An excellent session for India. They have taken 5 wickets in the morning, conceding 95 runs. India have kept Australia to well under 400 and the inexperienced bowling attack deserves praise for doing well. However, it was also a decent effort by the Australian tail, with the bat.

OUT! TIMBER! Natarajan finishes things off for the Indians. A lovely ball from Natarajan. Another fine bowling change from Rahane. A fuller ball around off, Hazlewood looks to drive but fails to make any connection. The ball goes behind to disturb the woodwork. Australia are bowled out for 369.
T Natarajan is back into the attack. Can he clean up either of these two?
A length ball around off and middle, Hazlewood looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Floated outside off, left alone.
Flat and around off, Starc blocks off his front foot.
4 dots in a row! This one is pitched outside off, turns away as Starc shoulders arms.
Darted outside off again, left alone again.
Another one which is wide outside off, Starc lets it go again.
Floated outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Boundary to finish the over. Full and wide outside the off pole zone, Hazlewood moves to the on side and caresses it through the gap in the covers. Nobody moved an inch there.
Another short ball around off, Josh lets it be.

FOUR! Nicely played there. Shortish length ball, Josh Hazlewood stays leg side of the ball and hits it through the covers. Long chase for the fiedler there but the ball gets into the boundary before he can cut it off.
Banged short but outside off. Hazlewood lets it be.
Short and outside off, Hazlewood looks to upper cut but misses.
Shortish and around off, tucked through square leg for one.
Solid in defence. Full length delivery, Hazlewood comes on the front foot and blocks it out.
Full and angled into the off stump line, nudged through mid on for one.
Full length ball, around the off stump, driven to cover. Apparently Lunch is approaching but can be extended by 30 minutes, as there is just 1 wicket left to fall, if it does not fall by then.
Outside off, Hazlewood lets that be.
Full length delivery on the off pole line, Josh comes forward and fends it out, back to the bowler.
Flatter and around the off pole, pushed down to long off for a single.
Full and on middle, flicked hard but straight to mid on.
Fired full on the pads, Josh looks to flick but misses.

In the air... safe! Good effort from Mayank. Short ball around off, this time Starc looks to pull but gets a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards mid on. Agarwal from mid off runs for the catch but he fails to get there, in spite of throwing himself.
Good length and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Banged short. Starc lets it go.
Beaten! Fullish and just around off, Starc looks to play it on the up but misses.
Fired full and on the pads, Josh flicks but finds square leg.
Full again, blocked.
Flat and around off, bunted on the on side.
Full and around off, Josh comes on the front foot to defend.
Tossed up and outside off, driven well but straight to short cover.
Floated around off, Hazlewood defends it easily.
Banged short for Starc, who lets it be as it goes well over. Pant does well to leap high and make a half stop. Could've raced away to the fence otherwise.
Full and around off, pushed through the cover-point region for one.
Good bouncer again. It is around off and middle but Hazlewood does well to move out of the way again.
Banged short and around off, Hazlewood sways away from the line.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off.
Length ball around off, kept out.
No. Starc is happy to block the looped up ball outside off.
Full and on off, driven to mid off for one. What will Starc do on the last ball? Will he go for the big shot?
Flat and around middle, kept out.
Beaten! Floats this one just outside off, it spins away a touch and beats the outside edge of Hazlewood, who prodded forward and looked to have a poke at it.
Josh Hazlewood is the last man in for Australia. Can Washington Sundar close it off in this very over?

OUT! Knocks him over from round his legs. Top delivery from Sundar. He gets his 3rd wicket of the game and the entertainment from Lyon is over. A handy knock nonetheless from him. Sundar fires it full and on middle and leg, Lyon once again gets down and looks to sweep. This time it is quicker too and he misses. The ball disturbs the stumps. End of Lyon and end of a very good stand between him and Starc.
Floated down the leg side, Lyon looks to sweep but misses.
Back of a length and around off, Starc lets it go to the keeper.
Good length and around off, tapped towards the cover fielder.
Short ball around off, pulled to deep square leg for a run.
Slips this one down the leg side. Lyon looks to flick but misses.

In the air... safe! Top work from Natarajan near the ropes. A short ball outside off, Starc goes for the pull but ends up getting a top edge. The ball goes towards fine leg and goes towards the fence. But but.. Natarajan, from fine leg, runs to his left, makes a lot of ground and does really well to stop the ball. They take just a run.
Fuller ball around middle to begin the new spell from Siraj. Starc pushes it hard but finds mid on.
So, Shardul is off after a decent spell and Mohammed Siraj comes back on. 24-10-64-1 for Mohammed Siraj. Can he clean up the last two wickets?
Looped up outside off, Starc drives it down to long off and keeps the strike for the next over.
Two more! Fuller and on middle, it is clipped through mid-wicket for two. 350 up for the Aussies. The stand moves to 36 off just 31.
Flat and around off, this time he stays back to block.
Floated around off, Starc comes foward to block.
Tossed up and outside off, Starc looks to drive but the ball takes a thickish outside edge and goes wide of gully. Two taken before the fielder can get to the ball.
Tossed up and outside off, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Shortish and just outside off, Starc leaves it alone.
Banged short, pulled down to deep square leg for an easy single.

FOUR! SHOT! Everything is coming off the middle of the willow of Lyon here. Fullish and outside off, Lyon drives it on the up. It goes to the right of the mid off fielder. It teases the fielder who gives it a chase and he ends up coming second in the race to the ropes.
Short and wide outside off, Lyon reaches out and throws the bat at it but makes no connection.
Short ball around middle, pulled down to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Two more for Starc and Australia. A length ball around off, Starc punches it through mid off and gets a brace.
On middle, Lyon defends it out.
Fuller and quicker, around off, kept out towards mid on.
Good running! Flatter and around middle, Lyon clips it through mid-wicket and scampers back for two.
Down the leg side, left alone.

Lyon sweeps again and takes down the short leg fielder. Shaw, the substitute is the man, who takes the blow on his knee. Luckily though, for India, he is back up and good to continue. We say lucky because even though he is a sub, India cannot afford to bring on new chaps onto the field now, even to replace subs. They are that injury plagued it seems.
FOUR! Lyon moves to 15 in just 9 balls. Useful runs. A tossed up ball around off, Lyon sweeps and hits it nicely through short fine leg. A boundary. The man at 45 dived but could not keep it out.
Short ball around off, Lyon pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
Beaten! Lovely from Thakur. Angles the length ball from outside off, Lyon looks to defend but the ball comes back in and beats the inside edge.

Huge appeal but turned down. A length ball around off, Lyon looks to defend but the ball comes back in nicely. He misses to get hit on the pad. They appeal but not out says the umpire. Maybe it hit him high on the pads. Also, some bat.
Length ball around off, kept out.

FOUR! Consecutive boundaries. Lyon with a shot that most of the batters in the world will be proud of. A fuller ball around off and middle from Shardul. Lyon just meets it with a full blade and strokes it through mid on. He enjoyed that shot too.
FOUR! Pulled away! Lyon won't mind taking the bowler on here. Shardul runs and bangs it short. Lyon swivels and nails the pull through backward square leg for a boundary.

SIX! There goes Starc. It was just a matter of time before Starc goes for the big shots. After blocking the 5 balls of the over, he decides that the time is now. Sundar tosses it up again. It is right in the hitting arc of Starc. The southpaw thumps it over long on for a biggie.
Full and around off, Starc drives it towards mid off.
Tossed up and around off, pushed to mid off.
Short and wide outside off, Starc cuts but finds backward point.
Floated around off, Starc punches it towards the mid off fielder.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Shortish and around off, punched on the off side. And it is end of another successful over for Thakur and India.
Lyon's off the mark in his 100th Test match. A short ball around off, Lyon pulls it through square leg leg for a brace.
THE GOAT STEPS OUT TO BAT! Nathan Lyon is in his 100th Test match, although expect the impact to be more with the ball. Can he though spring a surprise with the bat?

Pat has reviewed it! It is for a LBW appeal which ruled him out, on-field. Looks plumb, especially if there was no bat. Nothing on the Hot Spot and neither on Snicko. Ball Tracker is in, impact is inside and wickets are hitting. Australia lose the review.

OUT! LBW! Three reds! Shardul gets another one. India storming back in this game here. Superb stuff from Shardul here. He bowl this one full and straight. Cummins looks to flick but misses to get pinned on the pads, right in front of the wickets. They all go up in appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Looked dead plumb but Cummins reviews. Replays roll in and they show that Cummins is a gonner because Hot Spot detects no spike, so too did Snicko, and Ball Tracker shows three reds. Australia lose 3 wickets for 4 runs.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, Starc flicks it through mid-wicket to open his account.
Fuller and around off, driven through the covers for a single.
Full and around off, Starc pushes it towards mid off. Another successful over for India.
Mitchell Starc steps out to bat now. He can be aggressive with the bat. Even a little cameo and the Australians would be happy with that.

OUT! TIMBER! Lovely from Sundar. Green is the man who falls now. India get rid of both the set batters in back-to-back overs. Tosses the ball up and lands it around middle, Green looks to defend but the ball spins away just a touch and beats his bat. He played for the turn but missed the ball completely. The ball though goes onto hit its mark. Maybe there was an outside edge there. Green falls 3 short of his half ton.
Full and on middle, flicked to short mid-wicket for nothing.
Cummins is underway! Loopy ball outside off, he pushes it through the covers region for a single.
Full again, this one is stroked down to long on for one.
Full and around off, kept out.
Length and around off, Cummins blocks it on the leg side. End of a successful over from Shardul.
Length ball just around off, Cummins has his sticks covered as he shoulders arms.
Beaten again! Full and wide again from Thakur. Cummins throws his bat without moving his feet. Makes no connection.
In the channel outside off, left alone by Cummins.
Time for the tail. Will India curtail it? Or will it wag? Let's find out as Pat Cummins is the new batsman.

DRINKS! A much-needed breakthrough for the Indians just as the first hour of play on Day 2 was dawning to a close. Tim Paine and Cameron Green were looking strong, the former got to his half century in the last over and Thakur, the first bowling change of the day, has snared the Australian skipper. Now, India need to clean up the tail before it wags. The task is not done yet and they know that pretty much.

OUT! TAKEN! Shardul strikes. A much-needed wicket for the Indians. Superb from Shardul. He runs in and lands a fuller ball outside off from wide of the crease. Paine has been looking for the scoring opportunities. He sees the length and a bit of width too. He looks to go for the drive through the covers but the ball shapes away, just a tad bit, but it is enough to induce an outside edge. It goes to the right side of Rohit Sharma at second slip. It goes quickly but Rohit is alert there to gobble the chance. His 3rd catch of the innings. 50 and gone for Paine. He surely had a chance to score a Test ton here but he has thrown away the opportunity.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, driven to mid off for nothing.

FIFTY FOR PAINE! A fine, fine knock from the skipper. He has done really well here. He has copped up a fair bit for his batting but the skipper has led from the front here. A fuller ball outside off, Paine drives it wide of the cover fielder to get to the milestone. His 9th half ton in Test, second in this series. Can the Aussie skipper get to the three-figure score here?
Full and on middle, flicked wide of mid on for one.

Edged? Dropped? Yes, big edge! Luck for Green. Floats this one around off, it bounces a touch extra as Green looks to defend but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball then goes to the right of the keeper and hits him on the thigh pad. The ball lobs in the air off that deflection but drops well short of Rahane at first slip.
Full and on middle, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Sundar floats the first ball down the leg side. Green lets it be.

Washington Sundar is back here. 22-4-63-1 are his figures so far. It is a big task to graduate from First Class cricket to international cricket and Sundar is also the frontline spinner for his side, in the absence of Ashwin.
Around off on a good length, left alone.
Length ball outside off, Paine watches it go to the keeper.
Length ball around off, pushed to mid on.
Full and on middle, Green flicks it down to fine leg for one.
Quick single! Fullish and around middle, it is pushed just wide of the man at mid-wicket. Paine judges the single well and gets to the other end.
Good length and around off, Paine lets it be.
Shortish and outside off, Green keeps it out.
Length ball around middle, Green clips it towards mid-wicket. Thinks for a run but decides against it.
Length ball around middle, it is tucked through square leg for one.
Around off on a length, played back to the bowler.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Good length and around off, Green flicks it through mid-wicket. It is racing towards the fence but the mid-wicket fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to three.
This one is on a good length but again outside off. Easily left alone by Paine. 4 from Thakur's first over this morning.
Full again and it is just wide outside off. Paine is not interested again.
Full and just outside off, moves away a touch as Paine allows Pant to collect the ball behind the sticks.
Fullish and outside off, Paine once again shoulders arms.
Gets the line right. This one is just outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Thakur is welcomed with a boundary. Full and on the pads, easy for Paine. He whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Australia cross 300. Paine moves to 47.
Shardul Thakur is back on now. 18-5-67-1. Sanjay Manjrekar (on air) reckoned that the Palghar lad was very expensive on Day 1, even though he snared Marcus Harris early on. Can he make amends now?
Banged short but this one is too short and the line is down the leg side. Green sits under it.
Length ball around middle, it is tucked through square leg. A single.

What happened there? A fuller ball around off, Paine blocks it back to the bowler. Siraj picks the ball and takes a moment or two to have a shy at the stumps at the striker's end. He misses. Replays later on show that had he hit, Paine would've been on his bike back to the pavilion.
Another close leave! But Paine is trusting the bounce here. It is on a length and outside off, it comes back in. Paine shoulders arms and allows the ball to go over the stumps.

Tight leave! That wasn't too far away from the off pole. Good from Pant too. A length ball, pitched outside off, comes back in sharply as Paine lets it be. Pant had to dive to his left to gather the ball.
Good length and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Gets a long way across here. It was a length delivery and Green pushes it down to mid off. Says no to his skipper, for a single.
Full length ball, Green looks to drive again but ends up getting an inside edge onto his boots.

EDGED.... FOUR! Oh... Nick Knight (on air) reckons that there should have been a third slip there. Sanjay Manjrekar (on air) too concurs with that. Full length delivery, Cameron comes forward and goes for the drive. Ends up getting an outside edge and the ball flies between slips and gully, where third slip would have been, down to the third man fence.
This time T angles it in on off and middle, Tim stabs it to the short mid-wicket region. Says 'yeah yeah' and crosses.
Another leave as it was outside the off pole area.
TN comes 'around the wicket and bowls it full and outside the off stump channel, watchfully left alone.
Shortish and around off, kept out.
Length ball on the pads, Paine looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball rolls on the leg side and they cross for a leg bye.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Banged short and on middle and leg, Paine sits under it. Looked like he wanted to have a go at it first but opted against it later on.
Shortish and just outside off, left alone.
Good length and around off, Paine lets it be. The ball moves away a touch as it went past the batsman.
Maiden from T Natarajan too as Green blocks the last ball around off on a good length off his front foot.
Back of a length and angling away. Green lets it be again.
In the channel outside off, left alone this time.
Goes past the bat again. Lovely fron Natarajan. Bowls a full ball outside off, lures the batter into the drive. Green does that away from his body only to get beaten.
Good leave! Very good leave! Green has figured out that there is extra bounce on the surface. A length ball around off and middle, Green lets it be.
Fuller and around the pads, Green looks to flick but makes no connection.
Shortish and around off, Paine gets on top of the bounce and pushes it towards point. A maiden from Siraj.
Wide outside off, left alone.

Lucky! Paine is lucky here! A length ball again, just around off, Paine stays rooted to the crease and looks to cut but ends up getting a bottom edge. The ball bounces in front of the stumps and then goes to the keeper. Could've easily dragged it onto the stumps.
Another length ball around off, this one is pushed towards mid on.
Fullish and wide outside off, asking Paine to go for the drive but the Aussie skipper is not keen.
Good length and around off, moves a touch away but Paine does well to read it and block.
Shortish and on the off pole zone, pushed back to the bowler, who sticks his hand out. Makes a half-stop as it goes down to mid off further. But no runs result.

That works for the bowler. He has got the batsman to drive away from the body there. On a fuller length, in the zone outside off, Green drives it away from the body but finds the fielder at cover there.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and on the middle pole, defended solidly.
Shortish length ball on top of leg, takes Paine by surprise there, after pitching. The bounce. Paine hops and just about tucks it on the on side and gets to the other end.
Length ball around the off pole channel, dabbed on the off side.
... Day 2, Session 1....
The physio is out to attend to Rishabh Pant here. The magic spray has done its job and we are good to continue now...

No Ball. Another no ball from Natarajan, he needs to be a bit careful here. He bowled quite a few on Day 1. Fullish length delivery well outside the off stump line, TP goes after that but misses. Rishabh dives to his right and half-stops that. The slip cordon mops it up further. Hmm... the physio might have to come out to examine Pant here. He looks to be in some discomfort.
Runs flowing for Australia since the start of play in the morning. Good length delivery on off and middle, Tim Paine clips it behind square on the leg side and takes a run.
Length delivery around the off stump line, pushed down to the right of mid off for one.

FIVE OFF WIDES! Perhaps an indication of how the pitch might behave on Day 2. Short length ball but it pitches and goes way over the batsman's head, Pant leaps but the ball evades him and gets into the long stop fence for four. Wide called for the height as well. So five runs off extras.
On off, tapped down to mid on.
Shortish length delivery outside the off stump, Green stands tall and looks to defend from within the line, misses though.
Good length ball on off and middle, Paine knocks it to the mid-wicket region and takes a single.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...
Short length delivery but down the leg side, Tim lets that one through. Starts off a bit wayward, Mohammed.
Will it be Mohammed Siraj from the other end to continue? Yes, it is him. 19-8-51-1 to him so far.
FOUR! Drive again. On a full length and around the off pole line, Cameron just pushes that wide of mid off and the ball has enough timing on it to race away to the boundary.
Swing and a miss! Full and well outside the off pole, CG goes chasing after that, only to miss.
FOUR! This is brilliant. This is good cricket overall. Full length and on off and middle, Cameron Green drives that straight back past the bowler and gets a boundary.

BEATEN! An absolute beauty. An appeal from Natarajan for the caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. Notwithstanding that though, it was a peach of a delivery. Good length delivery around off, Green looks to block that off the front foot but misses and the ball goes past his outside edge to Rishabh. An appeal from the bowler, but in vain.
Full length ball well outside off, Cameron is not interested in having a poke at that.
Full length delivery on middle, blocked.

Right then, all set for the morning session! The Indian players are already out in the middle and Cameron Green and Tim Paine walk out to the middle as well. Remember, the second new ball is just 6 overs old. T Natarajan will resume with the ball. And, here he comes...

Weather update - Harsha Bhogle quickly alludes to the weather, as to what is in store for today. He says that conditions right now are dry and sunny but expects little bit of thunderstorms in the afternoon time.

Washington Sundar, who made a wonderful debut, has been caught up for a chat. He says that the first day of Test cricket, for him, was very good. Reckons it was good also for India. States that it is a privilege to be playing for India and that he loves bowling here. Thanks the management for giving him ample time earlier, to prepare in the nets. Feels that he had a couple of very good months preparing for the tour. Says that he got to know just before the start of the game that Ravichandran was not going to feature and that he was going to play. Adds that it is an emotional time back home as he is making his Test debut. Reckons that the wicket of Steven was a very big one. On how he feels about the game being poised, Washington says that a couple of wickets early on Day 2 could really help them.

Pitch Report - Glenn McGrath reckons the pitch is drier than normal and expects more cracks to open up. Feels the cracks will open up in the middle of the wicket. Wants to wait and gauge the impact of those cracks. Harsha Bhogle says that the pitch might quicken up on Day 2, quoting Allan Border, to which Glenn agrees.

For the Australians, it is all about crossing the 400-run mark and the larger part of that goal can only be achieved if the pair of Paine and Cameron stay around for a good while. The partnership between the two is worth 64 and they have been positive in scoring runs as well. But both might adopt a fairly toned-down approach, chosing to play the first session rather carefully. Should be interesting to watch. The other major thing is the weather! Hope it stays clear and that we get a good day's play....

From an Indian perspective, it was a decent day. Could have been better had they latched onto the catching opportunities as and when they came by but given the naivety in the bowling attack, it was a fairly good effort. If they are able to send back either of Paine or Green quickly, then they can make quick inroads into the tail. May not be as easy as said, but they would definitely fancy having a quick crack at the Aussie tail.

Hello and welcome to our coverage of the final Test between India and Australia. In case you missed all the action on an entertaining Day 1, worry not as we have you covered on that and what to expect on Day 2...

Australia will want to keep batting and probably cross the 400-run mark. India, on the other hand, need wickets. They can't let Australia get over the 350-run mark. Can they do so? We will find out on Day 2. Do join us at 10 AM local (12 AM GMT). Until then, cheers and take care.

India did have their chances, they got the openers early on, they then let it loose as they failed to build pressure on Labuschagne and Wade. When the chances came by, they failed to grab and that costed them dearly. They though did manage to fight back strongly as they got rid of the two set batters in quick succession. Could have had Green too, had Thakur held onto a caught and bowled chance. However, that drop chance may also cost them as he is now well set and is looking promising along with his skipper.

Have to say, it is Australia who will be happier of the two sides at the end of the day. Had India taken the chances that came to them, the story well could have been different. For now though, the hosts are on top courtesy a couple of good partnerships. A brilliant 100-run stand between Labuschagne who was the star with the bat and Wade and an on going stand between Paine and Green which is looking dangerous.
Siraj finishes with another bouncer on middle, Paine knows what he has to do. Just ducks under this one. With this, IT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Ohhh..worth a try! Bumper on middle, Tim Paine just sits under this one.
On the middle pole this time, Green tucks this one to mid-wicket and they cross over with a single.
Short of a length and around off, Green is aware of his off stump as he lets this one be.
On a length and on middle, clipped through square leg and the batters collect a brace.
Back of a length and around off, CG keeps this one out.
Outside off, no shot offered to this delivery on this occasion.
FOUR! Paine says thank you very much! You don't offer a gift to him and expect him to just deny it. Shorter again outside off, Paine clobbers this one through cover-point to find the ropes again.
On the pads, clipped to the fine leg region for a single.

FOUR! Better length this time around but he gets punished! Slightly overpitched on off, Green leans into the shot and creams his drive through cover-point to find the ropes. Agarwal gives chase but loses the race.
Slightly shorter and wide outside off, Paine slashes this one through cover-point and collects three runs.
Outside off, TP leaves this one alone.
Good length delivery outside off, again, Green just lets this one be.
Outside off, no shot offered by Green.
Short of a length and outside off, Green looks to have a poke at this but he misses.
Outside off, left alone.

Siraj appeals for LBW but turned down. A back of a length and around off and middle, Green looks to tuck thisone away but misses to get hit high on the pads. There is an excited appeal from Siraj, and not a lot of other Indian players. No says the umpire. Height could have been the issue there.
Outside off, not played at by Green.
On the pads, Paine looks to tuck it away but it takes the inside edge, hits the pads and then rolls to the leg side.
On off, blocked to mid off.
They have run four runs again. On the body, flicked to deep square leg and by the time, the fielders can run in and collect, the batters run four runs.

An excited enquiry by Pant but nor the umpire, nor Rahane is too convinced. A length delivery around off, Paine looks to have a poke at this one away from the body but misses. Pant collects and appeals. Nothing from the umpire. Rahane, too is not going to go for the review.
FOUR! DISPATCHED! No bounce on this one and it is easily send to the ropes by the skipper! A back of a length ball on off, Paine swivel-pulls this one to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
SLASH AND A MISS. A back of a length delivery outside off, Paine looks to cut this one away but gets done by the extra bounce and he misses his slash.
Another length ball to end! Kept out.
Back of a length and on middle, it is kept out with ease.
Back of a length again on middle, defended.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery! This is a back of a length ball, it pitches and holds its line. Green pokes for it and is beaten.
Back of a length and on middle, it is defended.
Length and outside off, it is nicely left.
Mohammed Siraj to bowl from the other end. 16-6-48-1 are his figures so far. Can he strike gold with the new ball in hand?
A single to end! A full ball on off, this is hit towards mid off. The fielder there dives to his right and half stops it. Can't stop the run.
On the stumps, another solid defense.
On middle, Green pushes it to mid on.
Outside off, not played at.
The cutter, it lands on off on a length, moves away after landing. Green is beaten.
Outside off, it is not played at.
Looks like India have decided now to take the new cherry. T Natarajan is back on now to speed in with the new ball.
FOUR! 250 up in style! Shorter and outside off, Paine stays back and guides it nicely through point for a boundary.
On middle, Paine once again is happy to play it off the back foot. He works it to mid-wicket.
Fires it on middle, Paine stays back and keeps it out.
Quicker and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
It is fired on the pads, Paine works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended.
A leave to end the over as this is bowled outside off.
On middle, blocked.
Right then. India now have the option to take the new ball. But it looks like they are not going to take it now.
Back of a length and on off, takes off after landing. Green looks to push at it but is beaten.

DROPPED! Green now has a life! Sharp chance but it came at a good height for the bowler. Should have hung on. This is fuller and on off, Green strokes it back uppishly but firmly to the left of the bowler. Thakur gets two hands to it but spills it. Labuschagne made India pay when he was dropped. Will we see something similar?
On middle, fuller, it is driven to mid off.
On a length and around off, defended.
FOUR! Swept and swept away fine! Floated around leg, Paine sweeps this one through the short fine leg region, into the fine leg fence. A good way to end the over.
Flatter and outside off, Paine cuts this one through backward point and the ball runs towards the ropes. Two runs, in the end.
Goes on the back foot and defends it back towards Sundar.
Loopy and on middle, TP works this one to the mid on region.
Flatter and on middle, tucked to the leg side.
On middle, kept out.
Way outside off, Green just lets it be.
Outside off, left alone.
Green does not feel interested in playing at this delivery which is outside off.
Length and around off, Green keeps this one out.
Outside off, left alone.
Three! Length and on off, Paine drives this one through the mid on region and by the time the fielder can chase and pull it behind the ropes in the deep. Three runs are collected.
Short and around off, Paine shuffles and punches this to the cover region. One run to end the over.
On off, blocked out.
Flighted and around off, Paine blocks it back solidly.
Flatter and on middle, tucked to square leg.
The groundstaff come out now to check something with the turf. The pitch has to be flattened a bit, near the run-up of the bowlers. The work is done and we are ready to resume.
On off, worked to the leg side.
On off, worked to the right hand side of Sundar, who fields it in his followthrough.

Length and on middle and leg, Green looks to flick but misses. Pant, though does well to dive to his left and stop the ball. Thakur makes a half-hearted appeal for caught behind but no says the umpire.
On off, punched to mid off.
Length and outside off, Green has no issues in leaving this one alone.
Good shot but a wonderful stop from Siraj as well. On a length around off, Paine smacks this one through the cover region and Siraj dives to his left and stops a certain boundary.
Good length and on off, Paine looks to tuck this one away but the ball comes off the inner half of the willow and hits his pads and rolls to the leg side.
Outside off, no shot offered to this delivery.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket. 6 runs off this over.
Now comes on the front foot and defends it back towards Washington.
On off, pushed back to Sundar.
On middle, worked to the leg side again for one more run.
On middle, clipped through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Beautiful use of the feet! Floated around off, Green puts on his dancing shoes and lofts this one over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Maiden over. On off, tapped to point. Paine comes forward but then raises his blade and yells 'NO' for the single.
Thakur is shaping this one away well. Full and around off, nipping away slightly, Paine pushes it back to the bowler.
Good leave by Tim. Shardul brings this one closer to the off pole, Paine raises his blade and lets this one through to the keeper.
Slightly behind the good length, some outswing noticed again, outside off, Paine shoulders arms to this one.
Full and around off, punched to the mid off fielder.
Outside off, Tim Paine leaves it alone.
Shardul Thakur (14-3-63-1) comes back on.
Quicker and on middle, Green pushes it to mid on.
On middle, it is kept out.
On the leg pole, this is worked towards mid-wicket again.
A single as Paine works it with the turn through mid-wicket.
On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Paine comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. He pushes it to mid on.
Well driven but straight to the fielder at mid off. Thakur fumbles to collect on the first try but it does no result in a run being taken.
Another solid defense offered by Green to the leg side.
On off, tucked to the leg side.
Changes his length and bowls this full delivery on off, Paine pushes this to the right of mid off to cross ends with his partner.
Short of a length delivery outside off, Tim hops and pushes this one towards the mid off region.
Three! On a length around off, Green slams this one through mid on and he will collect three runs as Siraj does well to chase after it and pull it back, just before the ropes.
Another one on middle, blocked.
Tossed up on off, Paine lunges and keeps it out.
Green now take a run as this is worked towards long on.
On off, it is defended nicely.
On off, Paine works it with the turn towards long on for one.
FOUR! Nice and fine! That loosener will release the pressure that was building. On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side and it races away to the fence.
Washington Sundar is back on. 16-4-39-1 are his figures so far. Can he send one of the batters back to the pavilion?

DRINKS. The last Drinks break of Day 1 and you would say things are pretty even at the moment. Even though Wade and Labuschagne were dictating the tempo and Marnus also reached his ton in that process, both of them fell, victims of the debutant Natarajan. Now, there are tow new batters out for the hosts and this is the perfect opportunity for India to come out on top and pick at the wickets. Will they be able to do so or will Australia fend off the challenge until stumps? Stick around to find out...
BEATEN AGAIN! This one is angled into the off pole, pitches and straightens. Beats the bat of Green who tries to defend.
BEATEN! Bowls the tempter. Green senses an opportunity to score some runs which is hard to come by. He goes after it but is beaten.
On middle, it is kept out nicely.
Another no ball! This one tails back in from outside off, Green gets a thick inside edge as he tries to flick. It goes towards deep backward square leg for two.
Good length and on off, Green defends it onto the ground.
Shorter and on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Bowls it fuller and on off, it is pushed to mid off.
One more maiden! Shorter and around off, this is guided to point.
Length again and on middle, Paine pushes it towards mid on.
Pushes Paine onto the back foot. He pushes it to mid on.
Another one on a length, Paine pushes it to mid off.
Length and on off, Paine is solid in defense.
Back of a length and on middle, Tim stands tall and defends it onto the ground.
Fuller and on off, Green pushes it back to the bowler.
Length and on off, Green is solid in defense.
On middle, Green lunges and keeps it out.
Nicely played! Waits for this length ball and then guides it through backward point. Two taken.
On the middle pole, Green works it to mid-wicket.
Good length and on middle, it is kept out nicely.
Maiden by Siraj. A length delivery angling in to the right-hander, well blocked out towards gully by Paine.
Short of a length and around off, Tim fends this one out to the cover region.
On off, the captain blocks this one.
Length ball, fairly wide, left alone by Paine.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off.
Another delivery outside off, left alone.
Outside off, left alone by Green.
The skipper, Tim Paine is in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Natarajan has scalped his second wicket in his maiden Test game and he gets the big, big wicket of Labuschagne, who did not want to stop batting, by the looks of things. A huge wicket for India. Just when you thought Australia were running away with the game, India comes back and grab two quick wickets. This is a shortish length delivery around off, Labuschagne looks to pull but once again is done in by the extra bounce. The ball takes the top edge and lobs near the short fine leg area. Pant calls for it, keeps his eyes on the ball and takes a good catch. So the extra bounce seems to be troubling the Aussie batters. Two well-set batters getting out in a similar manner. Two new batters out there now on a wicket which is not that easy to begin on. Can India make full use of it? Can they take another quickly? They are right back into the game.
Length and on off, pushed to point.

Back of a length this time, around off, Marnus hooks this one to the deep mid-wicket region and a fumble by the fielder in the deep, sees the batters run back for the second run. Good awareness shown by the batters.
Outside off, worked to cover-point.
Another instance where the batters run four runs. Slightly shorter and on off, ML pulls this one through square leg and the batters run four before the fielder can mop up in the deep.

FOUR! CLASSY! Excellent way to start your innings! Plays this one down the ground with ease. Fullish length ball outside off, Green leans forward and drives this one through mid off and this time, he finds the ropes.
Green is off the mark here. Good length delivery, outside off, punched through mid off and he collects two runs.
Slightly behind the good length and outside off, Marnus slashes this one to the deep point region for a single.
On off, tucked to the mid on region, this time by Marnus.
Full length and around off, ML drives this one to the mid off region this time.
Length and on off, Marnus works it back to where it came from. Siraj half stops this one and the ball goes towards mid on.
Full and around off, pushed to the cover region again by Green. A good over for Natarajan comes to an end. Gets a wicket.
On off, pushed to the cover region.
Cameron Green walks out now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, India get the wicket that they were looking for and they have broken this partnership which was doing them much damage! Also, the first wicket for Natarajan in Tests. He will be really happy with this. Natarajan fires in a short ball on middle, Wade looks to pull this one but does not do so cleanly. It takes the top edge as the bounce gets big on him and lobs high in the air just in between mid on and mid off. Two fielders are running in and it looks like there will be some confusion and this chance will go by as well. But Thakur, who runs in from mid on, does well to take it, in the end. Wade departs for 45 and his fine knock comes to a close.
Shorter in length, outside the off pole, Wade slaps this one through cover-point and picks up a brace.
Short of a length and on off, Wade pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, pushed to covers.

HUNDRED FOR MARNUS LABUSCHAGNE. A very well deserved one. He has battled it out since the start and has played his strokes and has finally reached the triple digit mark in this series. He has been handed a couple of lives but he has used these opportunities to the fullest. He raises his blade and acknowledges the crowd as well. Length and outside off, Marnus slaps this one through the cover region and because of the big outfields, they are able to return for the 4th run.
Straying on the pads this time, Wade flicks this one through square leg again and collect one run. They think about two but the fielder in the deep is quick to collect and throw it back towards Pant.
On off again, Wade pushes this one to the leg side.
Length and on off, Wade pushes this one back towards Siraj.
On middle, tapped to the mid-wicket region.
FOUR! Runs are flowing freely now for the Australians! Another boundary! A full delivery on middle, Wade clips this one through the square leg region and he fetches a boundary.

FOUR! A wonderful on-drive! Labuschagne moves to 97 with that shot! Length and around off, Marnus stands tall and punches this one through the mid on region and even though a fielder gives it a chase, the ball wins the race to the ropes.
Outside off, on a good length, Marnus is not interested in having a poke at this. He is still on 93. Showing tremendous amounts of patience so far.
Good length delivery outside off, Labuschagne sways back slightly and looks to punch this one through the covers but the ball comes off the inner half of the blade and rolls to the off side.
Another solid defense towards the mid on region.
On a length and around off, Labuschagne taps this one to the off side. Is also quick to deny the single.
Full ball on off, Marnus pushes it back to the bowler.
Another two! Full and on middle, Wade works it through mid-wicket and takes an easy two.
Down the leg side, Wade lets it be.
Angled into the pads, from around the wicket, it is worked through mid-wicket for two. Runs coming easily now.
Down the leg side, Wade looks to work it on the leg side but misses.
Fuller and on the pads, Wade works it to mid on.

7 away from a ton now! Fuller and around off, Labuschagne just uses the pace of the ball and strokes it through mid off. Sundar runs after it, he initially thinks of a dive but then realizes it is not needed and just picks it up and throws it back. Three taken.
Back of a length and on off, Wade stays back and keeps it out.
Three! Once again Thakur overpitches and it is outside off. Labuschagne leans into it and strokes it through covers. Three.
Well wide outside off, Labuschagne does not play at it.
One more ball outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fuller and around off, it is driven nicely but to covers.
Outside off, Labuschagne lets it be.
On middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up ball on off, Marnus keeps it out.
On middle, Wade flicks it towards mid on for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Labuschagne guides it towards third man for a run.
Flighted ball on off, Labuschagne punches it through point for a couple.
Tossed up delivery on off, Wade drives it through mid off for a single.
Shorter and on middle, this is worked through square leg for one more.
Back of a length and on off, it is pushed towards the man at covers.
A little too straight, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one more.
Goes back to landing it on a length and outside off, not played at.
FOUR! Crisp! This is fuller and where Labuschagne likes it. He creams it through wide mid off and the ball races away to the fence.
Length and outside off, left alone.
A dot to end! On middle, Wade lunges and keeps it out.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle, this is defended.
Tossed up on off, Wade hits it nicely to mid off.
Good shot! Slightly shorter and around off, Labuschagne stays back and pushes it through covers for three.
On middle, this is worked to square leg.
On a length and around off, it is defended onto the ground.
On middle, Wade defends it nicely.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg. Easy two.
On the shorter side outside off, this is cut through point for one.
Just outside off, Marnus knows where his off pole is and lets it be.
Fuller, gets it to tail away a little. Blocked back to the bowler.
Outside off, Wade lets it go to the keeper.
Very full and on the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for a couple.
Flatter and on middle, Wade stays back and defends it onto the ground.
Fires this one outside off to the left hander. Left alone.
Labuschagne comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. He works it through mid-wicket for the first run of this session.
Flatter and on off, it is pushed towards cover.

We are back for the final session of Day 1. The Indian players stride out into the middle and spread out on the field. The batters for the hosts, Marnus Labuschagne and Matthew Wade come out as well. Washington Sundar to begin with the ball. Here we go...
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

India need a wicket to get back into this one. Had they taken the chances that came their way, they would have probably been on top in this game at the moment but they are still not far away from it. They know a wicket or two and it will see them get back on top. Will they fightback or will Australia win the last session too? Join us for the final session of Day 1 on the other side of the break.

A session which probably belongs to Australia! Yes, they did lose Smith but Labuschagne and Wade have done really well so far. The two are admist a 67-run stand and have scored at a decent rate too. Yes, the partnership has had its luck as we saw Labuschagne been dropped twice but take nothing away from the way the two have played. Australia will hope the two can continue batting, Labuschagne will be eyeing a ton and Wade too will want to make most of the start he has got.
Length and outside off, Marnus cuts this one towards the point region and crosses ends with his partner. With that, IT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Slightly closer to the off pole this time, but still nothing to be alarmed about for Labuschagne as he lets this one through to the keeper.
Full ball on middle, ML clips this one through mid-wicket and the batters pick up a single.
Well driven but it is straight to the fielder. Overpitched, slightly, around off, Labuschagne drives this one to the cover region and the fielder does well to save this one.
Outside off again, Marnus leaves it alone.
Outside off, good length delivery, Labuschagne just raises his blade and indicates that he has no interest in playing at this.
Flighted and on middle, Wade, again is solid in his defense.
Lunges forward and blocks this one, does Wade.
Loopy on off, Wade keeps this one out.
On off, pushed to the cover region.
On middle, clipped to the leg side for one. The fielder there takes the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end but he throws it straight into Rohit Sharma. Ouch. Would have stung, that.

FOUR! Labushchagne is looking to turn it on now! His third boundary from the last over. Floated on off, Marnus gets on his knees and looks to sweep but it takes the under edge and runs away to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Keeps a straight bat and defends this one out towards the mid off fielder.
Length and on middle. flicked to the square leg region. No run is the call and they do not go for a run.
On middle, worked to the leg side for one.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Marnus! He is making full use of the lives that he has been handed! Thakur drags the length back even more and this is a shorter one around off. Labuschagne swivel-pulls this one through sqaure leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Marnus dispatches this one! Short and on off, Labuschagne pulls this one through the mid-wicket region to find the ropes.

Half hearted appeal for this caught behind. A back of a length delivery around middle and leg, Marnus looks to pull this one away but misses and the ball goes to Pant, who takes it and appeals along with Thakur. The umpire shakes his head. Rahane, too, is not too keen on taking the review. Replays later show that this was a good call as it missed the bat and it came off the pad.
Floated on off, driven to mid off.
Prods forward this time and keeps this one out off his front foot.
Outside off, left alone.
Flighted and outside off, kept out to the off side.

Tossed up and around off, Marnus heaves this one towards covers and the fielder there dives to his left and stops the ball. Good work by him. Only a single. Also, brings up the 50-run stand between these two. Something that the Aussies needed after losing Smith.
Floated on leg, ML looks for the tuck away but misses and gets hit on the pads. A polite enquiry but no says the umpire.

FOUR! A gift to Wade, by Thakur and Wade accepts gleefully! A full toss outside off, Wade hammers this one through the extra cover region and though 2 fielders gave it a chase, it would not make a difference as the ball ran away to the ropes.
Another solid defensive push by Wade.
Length and on off, MW keeps this one out.

EDGY FOUR. Wade is the lucky person here. Goes in between the slip cordon and the gully fielder. On a length on off, Wade looks to block this one out with soft hands but the ball moves away ever so slightly and takes the outside edge. Goes just past the second slip fielder and into the third man fence for a boundary.
Shuffles across slightly towards the off side and blocks this one back towards Thakur.
On off, Wade pushes this back towards the bowler.
Shardul Thakur is back to bowl now. His figures so far read 7-3-27-1.
On off, kept out.

Flatter and outside off, Wade camps on his back foot and slams this one through the point region. Natarajan is the man who is giving this chase. It looks like the ball will win the race but Natarajan does well to pull the ball back before the ropes. Three runs.
Now comes on the front foot and blocks this one out.
Outside off, Wade does not play at this.
Short and around off, Wade pushes this one to the cover region.
Floated outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
The last ball is outside off, it is left alone.
FOUR! That is cracked! It is full and there to be hit. Labuschagne is not going to miss out. He strokes it through covers, the timing is good enough to bag a boundary.
Does what he should have on the last ball, leaves it alone as it is outside off.
Loose stroke! This is shorter and outside off, Marnus tries to cut away from the body but is beaten.
Angled into the middle pole, Marnus stays back and defends it nicely.
Outside off, it is not played at.

FOUR! SLAMMED! Wade finds the ropes now. Loopy and outside off, Wade smacks this one through the cover region and the fielder gives it chase and tries to stop the ball before the ropes but the ball wins the race to the ropes.
On middle, pushed to the leg side for a single.
Flighted outside off, Wade slams this one to the mid off region and collects a single.
On off, well kept out.

FIFTY FOR MARNUS LABUSCHAGNE. He has played well so far and has scored a good 50 for his side. Rode his luck slightly every now and then, but he has continued the good work with the bat. Floated on off, Marnus works this one through the mid on region for a single. He raises his blade to acknowledge the applause. But he will know that the job is not done yet and will be looking to get to that triple digit mark.
Floated on off, Marnus keeps this one out. His is on 49 now.
He moves onto 49 as he takes a single by working it through mid-wicket.

Is that a drop? It indeed has carried! Yes, it is a drop. A tough chance for Pujara though. Natarajan bowls this from around the wicket, it is on a length, pitches and then straightens from the off pole. Labuschagne plays the original trajectory but it goes off the outside edge between Pant and Pujara at first slip. Both dive, the keeper to his right and first slip to his left. It beats Pant and Pujara goes for it with one hand but the ball does not stick in. That needed to stay in. Another life for Labuschagne. Probably Pant and Pujara are standing way too deep. Had they been a little ahead, it could have been a little easier.
Labuschagne moves onto 48! Fuller and outside off, it is driven through covers, not right off the middle but for two.
Angles it into the pads, Labuschagne watches it carefully and then works it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, Labuschagne pushes it to covers.
Fuller and on off, it is pushed nicely to mid off. Another no ball. Seen quite a few from Natarajan.
One more delivery outside off, swings after going past the batter. Pant takes it nicely.
A dot to end a maiden! On middle, Wade is solid in defense.
Another one outside off, Wade lets it go.
Quicker and shorter, Wade goes back and pushes it towards cover.
Slightly slower this time and it is outside off again. Wade does not play at it.
Once again outside off, Wade does not play at it.
Outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.
On the fuller side, Labuschagne strokes it to mid off again.
Back of a length and on middle, Labuschagne stands tall and defends it.
Back of a length and on middle, Labuschagne goes back and defends it.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Angled into the pads, Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket.
That is a lovely delivery! This is angled in from left-arm around the wicket. It lands and then straightens from off. Labuschagne is beaten as he tries to defend.
On off, Wade lunges and blocks.
On off, this is pushed straight to the fielder at mid off.
On the pads, it is worked through square leg this time for one.
Continues to bowl the straighter line, this is worked to that fielder at backward square leg.
On the pads, shorter again, this is pulled to backward square leg again.
Sundar continues with the straightish line, it is worked to backward square leg.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! This is pure timing! Fuller and on off, Wade leans into it and strokes it nicely through covers for a boundary.
Some outswing, it is outside off, left alone again.
Outside off, left alone.
A little bit of tail back into the batsman. Wade tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Another one on a length and around middle, Wade works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter in length and on middle, Wade blocks it.
Another no ball from Natarajan! This is fuller and on middle, it is worked towards mid on, where the fielder dives to his right and stops it.
The sweep is out, it is hit through square leg for one.
Flatter and on middle, Wade lunges forward and keeps it out.
Down the leg side, it is left alone.
On off, this is defended nicely.
BEATEN! This is nicely tossed up on off, Wade looks to drive but the ball holds its line and beats the outside edge.
Shorter and outside off, Wade guides it to point.

DRINKS. India will be really glad with how the first half of the second session has gone by. They had to break the stand between Smith and Labuschagne and they have done just that. Sundar got his maiden Test wicket, when he got rid of the dangerous Smith. But the thing which would be disappointing India would be the fact that Saini has walked off the field after feeling some discomfort. They will look to pick up a couple more wickets before Tea and the hosts would want Labuschagne and Wade to see off the danger until Tea, at the very least.
Back of a length and on off, Labuschagne keeps it out nicely.
Length again, Labuschagne is standing well ahead of the crease. Blocked.
Outside off, Labuschagne lets it be.
Fullish and on middle, it is played to mid on.
Angled into the pads, this is worked around the corner for one.
Good length and on off, Natarajan defends it onto the ground.
Short and on middle, tucked to square leg.
Loopy on off, Marnus defends this one back towards Sundar.
Flatter around off, ML guides this one to point.
On off, blocked to the leg side.
Short and around off, Labuschagne rocks on his back foot and punches this one through the backward point region and the batters come back for the double.
Floated on off, nudged to the square leg region.
One more delivery down the leg side, Wade tries to flick but misses.
Three! A little too straight, this is worked through mid-wicket and three is taken. 100 up for the Aussies as well.
On middle, it is worked towards mid-wicket.
On middle, this is kept out nicely.
Extremely full and on the pads, Labuschagne looks to flick but misses. It hits him on the pads. An appeal but turned down.
Down the leg side, Labuschagne looks to flick but misses.
Shorter and on off, it is pushed towards cover for one.
T Natarajan is back into the attack. 6-1-8-0 are his numbers so far.
That delivery got Pant a little too excited! Nothing happened though! It is tossed up on off, Wade pushes it towards mid off for one.
On off, it is kept out.
An appeal but not sure why! This is on off, Wade looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pad.
On off, Wade defends it. A little bit of turn for Sundar.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
A short one is bowled outside off, it is slapped through covers for one.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Rahane is the culprit! That should have been taken! Huge, huge let off. Labuschagne is looking good and giving him a chance could prove very costly. It is a back of a length ball, it lands and then straightens. Labuschagne looks to defend but it flies off the outside edge towards gully. Rahane gets two hands to it but spills it.

Uh oh! Not something that the Indians would want to see. Saini is down and in pain. It seems that he has injured himself near the groin area. The physio is out and is having a look at him. Let's hope that this is nothing serious and he can continue. Not a good sign as Saini has WALKED OFF THE FIELD. Rohit Sharma to complete the over now.
Shorter and on middle, Labuschagne pulls it through square leg for two.
Angling down the leg side, it is left alone again.
Back of a length and on middle, it is defended.
Down the leg side, Marnus looks to flick but misses.

FOUR! Wade gets off the mark with a boundary! A good shot! He had some width to play with and he does not miss out. Short and outside off, Wade slashes his blade through this and the ball speeds away through point, for a boundary.
Short and around off, MW blocks this one out.
Flighted outside off, well driven to the cover fielder.
Floated on off, Wade pushes this one to the off side.
Floated outside off, Wade lets this one be.
Matthew Wade is in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sundar breaks this partnership and this is his first Test wicket. Does not get any bigger than this, gets the big fish, that is Smith. Sundar floats it up around off and middle, Smith comes forward slightly and flicks this one uppishly towards the short mid-wicket region. Rohit Sharma is the fielder there and he gets low and takes a delightful catch. You could also say that this is a soft dismissal. Smith looked like he was here for the long haul but his innings is cut short. Australia lose their third wicket.
Sundar is back on.
Outside off, guided to gully. Siraj concedes 5 runs off this over.

Gets on top of the bounce. Again, just behind that good length area outside off, Smith stands tall and slams this one through the cover region. Three taken by the time the fielder mops up in the deep.
Slightly behind the good length and around off, SS knocks this one towards mid on but for no runs on this instance.
On off, pushed towards mid on. One run.
'Catch' was the call by the Indian players but the ball fell way short of the man in the deep. Short and around off, Smith pulls this one towards the fine leg region and crosses ends with Marnus.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Good length and around off, ML is solid in his defensive stroke.
Will punch and get a single. Outside off, Smith goes on his back foot and punches this one through the cover region for one.
On off, kept out by SS.

Extra bounce on offer here. A short of a length delivery, on middle, Smith looks to fend this one out but the ball zips sharply after taking the deck, Smith does fend it out but it comes off the top part of the blade.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Starts the over off with a length ball around off, Smith pushes this one to the fielder present at mid on. 'No run', says Smudge to his partner.
Saini strays his line this time and bowls it full and on middle and leg, Marnus clips this one through square leg for a couple. 6 runs off this over.
Saini bowls this closer to the off pole this time and makes Labuschagne have a feel for it. He blocks it out well.
Similar delivery as the last ball, Marnus, again, just leaves this one by itself.
Length delivery but again this is outside off. Marnus does not think too much and just shoulders arms to this one.
On off, pushed to mid on.

FOUR. This was a controlled stroke by Marnus. Waited on the ball and then dispatched this one. Shortish and on middle, Labuschagne swivel-pulls this one through the mid-wicket region and the ball speeds away to the advertisment triangles.
Length, on middle, pushed to square leg. A loud and clear 'No' is heard from Smith as he does not want to take the single.
On off, tucked to the leg side.
Full length delivery outside off, Marnus pokes this one towards covers and decides to give the strike to Smith.
On off, well kept out.
Another couple of runs. Bowls in a length ball on middle and leg, Labuschagne flicks this one to the right of fine leg again to collect a brace. Was in complete control of that stroke, was Marnus.
Angles in a length delivery, around the off pole, Marnus blocks this one out to the off side.
In the channel outside off, Smith raises his bat to let this one go. A maiden by Navdeep Saini.
Short of a length and around off, Smith pushes this one out towards the off side.
Outside off, Steven shoulders arms to this one.
On middle, worked to the leg side on this occasion.

Great shot and good fielding by Gill too. On a length, outside off this time, Smith leans forward and drives this one through the cover region but Gill does well to drive to his right and stop the ball.
Around off, good length, solid defense offered by Smudge.
On middle, Marnus flicks this one to the right of fine leg and by the time he can come across, Marnus completes two runs.
Darts in a length ball around off, helped towards the square leg fielder.
Good length delivery this time, around leg, well worked through the short fine leg region for a single.
On the pads, Smith looks to tuck it away but it takes the inside edge and hits hiim on the pads.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length and on middle, clipped to square leg.
Who will partner Saini with the ball from the other end? Mohammed Siraj.
On off, pushed back towards Saini.
Outside off, left alone by Marnus.
Down the leg side, Marnus misses his tuck away.

Wow, there was a bit of a mix-up but no harm, no foul for the hosts. They have run four runs. Yes, you read that right. But this happens in Australia, as the grounds are huge. Slightly too straight from Saini. Labuschagne clips this one through mid-wicket. Two fielders give it chase and pull it back before the ropes. The batters decide to run the fourth run. The throw is at the keeper's end and Pant collects and throws it towards Saini at the other end, but Smith dived and made it back in. So, four runs in total.

Appeal for LBW turned down! A length delivery around middle and leg, Marnus look to tuck this one away to the leg side but he misses and gets rapped on the pads. Saini appeals but the umpire is unmoved.
Back of a length delivery and around off, Marnus taps this one towards the fielder that was present at gully.
We are back for the second session. The batters for Australia, Steven Smith and Marnus Labuschagne stride out into the middle. Navdeep Saini to begin the bowling for the visitors. Off we go...
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

As far as the Indian bowlers are concerned, Siraj has been the pick hands down. He has bowled with great control and has looked threatening. Natarajan has been economical but harmless so far. Thakur has a wicket to his name but has been quite wayward. Sundar and Saini have started off decently. The pacers need to make the batters play more and be patient. The wicket is not offering a lot so patience is the key. Will the visitors regain control of the game after the break or will Australia move on top? Join us in a bit to know...

A good session for India but Australia have recovered really well courtesy the pair of Labuschagne and Smith. After the loss of the openers early, the two had done really well so far and amidst a solid stand. They look composed and in control at the moment. More of the same is what Australia will be wanting from the two.

A dot to end the first session. No shot played there. Flatter and down the leg side, Smith lets that one hit his pads and it takes the deflection and goes wide of the leg slip fielder. But a Dead ball is called. With that, IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 1!
On middle, worked to mid-wicket this time around.
Floated around off, Steven prods forward and blocks this one out off the front foot.
On middle, worked to the leg side again. He is shuffling around so that his front pad is out of the picture and he does not give any easy chances.
Another short delivery around middle and leg, Smith, again tucks this one to square leg.
Flat and around middle and leg, Smith shuffles and works this to square leg.
A length delivery around off, Labuschagne offers a solid defense to this one.
Identical delivery as the last ball, same kind of shot offered by Marnus and Saini does well to half stop this in his followthrough.
Length and around off, nips back in slightly, Marnus plays this one back towards Navdeep.
Outside off, left alone.

Gets a single this time. Saini goes fuller and on middle, Smith helps this one through short fine leg and crosses over for a single. Looks back to see if the double is one but it is not, so he settles for the single.
Full and on middle, Smith clips this but finds the man at square leg.
Another delivery around the leg pole, Labuschagne just pads this one away to the leg side. Another good over by Sundar.
Short and around the leg pole, Marnus lets this one be and gets hit on the pads.
On middle, worked to square leg.
On the pads, tucked to the short fine leg region.
Down the leg side, ML looks to tuck it away but he misses and Pant collects. He is the only one up in appeal but the umpire does not move.
Floated on middle, tucked to square leg. 'COME ON, WASHIIII', is what Pant is saying loudly behind the stumps, motivating the debutant.
Slightly short and around off, Marnus gets on top of the bounce and works this to square leg. The batters run across for a single to see the over off.
Back of a length and around off, Marnus moves across to the off side slightly and blocks this one out.
Another length delivery outside off, Marnus covers his off pole and leaves this one alone.
Outside off by Saini, left alone by Marnus.
Good running. Shortish and slightly wider, Labuschagne punches this one through the cover region and the batters run well and hard to come back for the double.
Slips this one down the leg side, Labuschagne looks to flick but misses.
Off the outer half! A good end to the over. It is on middle, once again drifts away a little and holds its line. Smith looks to block but it goes off the outer half towards point.

Extra bounce and that has hit Smith on the arm! He is in a little pain. The line is once again straighter. Smith looks to sweep but misses to cop a blow on the arm. Sundar is not one who is easy to sweep, he is bound to get some extra bounce because of his height.
On middle, Smith stays back and works it to square leg.
Slips this one down the leg side, Smith misses the pull. He is disappointed as he knew there were runs on offer there.
Again, the leg stump line, Smith once again works it to short leg.
Starts off with one on middle and leg. A little bit of drift away from the batter. It is worked to short leg.
Right. Time for the debutant and also some spin. Washington Sundar is going to bowl now.
A maiden to begin with by Saini but a harmless one. The last nut too is dished wide outside off, easy leave.
Slowly moving closer to the off pole but once again it is not close enough to make the batter play.
Harmless delivery again, well outside off, need not play at those.
Length again and outside off, Marnus leaves it in his unique way.
One more ball outside off, Marnus shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Labuschagne lets it be.
Navdeep Saini has been handed the ball now.

FOUR! Gets it wrong on the last ball! This is the problem with Thakur, he has not bowled with control. Bowled 5 good balls but let all the pressure ease away with a wide short one outside off. Smith cracks it through point and it races away to the fence.
Finding his lines and lengths here! Just outside off, in the 5th stump channel. Left alone.
Make that 4 now! On a length again and just on off, Smith is solid in defense.
Good three balls from Thakur! This is once again on a length and outside off, left alone.
Again, on a length and on off, defended.
Really good from Thakur! This is what he should be bowling. Length and around off, blocked.
On middle, it is defended. A maiden from Siraj.
On middle, Labuschagne works it with the angle to mid-wicket.
Makes the batter play this time, it is on off, Labuschagne gets right behind the line and defends it.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Does not angle it in enough to make the batter play.
And again, on off and on a length, defended.
Back of a length and on off, Labuschagne keeps it out. Siraj has been really good till now. He has hit the right lengths on a consistent basis.

FOUR! This one is exquisite! Wonderful! Thakur goes full again but this one goes straight on and it is an easy half volley. Smith creams it past mid off and it races away. Second boundary in the over. Another expensive one by Thakur.

FOUR! A loud shout of catch but it is in the gap! Fortunate boundary for Smith but he won't mind! Better from Thakur. He is really getting the ball to shape nicely. He bowls it full encouraging the drive. Smith does go for it but the away swing induces the outside edge, it goes uppishly but through backward point for a boundary. Smith had a relieved look on his face after he saw that go in the gap.
Labuschagne now gets one, it is a little too straight, he works it towards mid on for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Short and on the body, this is pulled down to fine leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, it is pushed to mid off.

FOUR! SHOT! That was an imperious on-drive! Treat to the eyes. A length ball on off, Labuschagne shows the full face of the blade as he drives this one through mid on and the ball speeds away to the long on ropes. A good way to end the over.
On off, blocked out.
A couple this time. Length and on middle, Marnus flicks this one through mid-wicket and by the time the fielder can clean up in the deep, they cross over for the second run.
BEATEN. Wonderful bowling by Siraj! A length delivery, around the off pole, Marnus looks to block this one out but he gets beaten.
Slightly more fuller and on middle, Smith works this to the fine leg region to return the favour to Labuschagne.
Angling into off and middle, Labuschagne flicks this one to the square leg region and rotates to give his partner, Smith the strike.
On middle, clipped to the right of square leg. 'WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, NO, NO', says Smith, as he knows that single will not be possible on this occasion.
On off, tucked to the wide mid on region. Quick, early call to deny the single, by Smith.
Another length delivery outside off, Smith raises his willow and does not play at this.
Short of a length and on off, Smith nudges this to the square leg region.
Outside off, left alone by Smudge.
EDGY. Ohhh...gets lucky, does Smith. A fuller length ball outside off, Smith looks to drive this one but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to the fielder present at square leg.
Another maiden by 'India's most experienced pacer' for this game. Outside off, not played at by Marnus.
Short of a length this time, around middle, pushed to the leg side.
Back of a length and on middle, clipped to the short fine leg region. No run on this occasion.
On a length around off, Labuschagne is solid in his push towards the cover region.
Down the leg side, leaves this one alone, does Labuschagne.
Angling into the off pole, Marnus blocks this one back towards Siraj.
Another leave as this one was bowled outside off.
Another length ball outside the off pole, Smith raises the white flag and shoulders arms to this one.
Length and around off, pushed to the cover-point region.
Outside off again, SS leaves it be.
Away movement noticed here again. On a length, around off, moving away from the right-hander, Smith blocks this one out solidly towards the off side.
On off, tapped to the cover region.
Outside off, not doing much harm to Marnus, who does not have a poke at this.
Shortish and on middle, pulled to the fielder stationed at mid-wicket.
On middle, worked to square leg. Again, Marnus is quick to deny the single.
Good length and around off, Labuschagne taps this to the cover-point region and is quick to yell 'NO RUNNNN'.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.

FOUR BYES. That one flew! A back of a length and on middle and leg, the bounce gets too big as Marnus misses his tuck. Pant dives to his left, but to no avail as the ball races away to the fine leg fence.

DRINKS, A good first hour of play, mostly for the visitors but the Australians are slowly coming back into the game as well. India will be happy with how things have started off as they have got two wickets very early on in the game. But now, they have the fearsome duo of Smith and Labuschagne out there and this is the pair which has troubled them the most in the previous Test. The hosts will be banking on them to help them steady the ship, after losing 2 quick wickets. India will want to scalp one or two more wickets before the Lunch break. Will they be able to do so? Let us find out....
Well outside off to end, left alone. Not a very good over from Shardul. He was struggling for both, line and length in this over and hence, it was a good one for the Aussies.
Smith has come out to bat with a lot of intent here! Two boundaries followed by a couple! This is on the pads, it is worked behind square on the leg side for two.

FOUR! SHOT! This is beautiful! Back-to-back boundaries and this is better than the last one. Yes, it is a half volley outside off but still needs to be put away and Smith does it in style. He leans into it nicely and creams it through covers.
FOUR! Whipped away! Not a very bad delivery but this is Smith's strength! It is fuller and on middle, looking to hit the pads of Smith. He whips it through wide mid on for a boundary.
Once again this is well outside off, harmless, left alone.
This time he gets the batter to drive! Fuller and on off, wanting it to shape away. Smith shows the full face of the bat and strokes it back to the bowler.
A leave to end as this is bowled outside off again. Too many harmless deliveries by the Indians with the new ball. Even Thakur from the other end has seen many of his balls left alone.

That was probably a half chance had Saini fielded it cleanly! It is a little too straight, this is worked towards mid on and Labuschagne goes for a tight run. The misfield though not only makes the first run easy but also gifts him a second.
Once again goes back to bowling it outside off, Marnus covers his off pole and lets it be.
Perfect! Length and on off, Labuschagne does well to shuffle across and block it.
Better! This is probably a little bit fuller. A little bit of movement through away from Smith. Smith is not in control of the drive. It goes off the outer half through covers for one.
Length and outside off, left alone. Natarajan has bowled too many deliveries which have been left. Needs to make the batter play a little more.
Another leave to end the over as it is once again bowled outside off.
Gets this one to shape away nicely. The line is outside off though. Not played at.
Good leave! This is on a length, it seems like the effort ball as it zips through. Outside off though and it is left alone.

BEATEN! That is a beauty! It is full and around off, shapes away late. Labuschagne goes after it away from the body. Gets beaten.
