Slight loss of concentration from Marnus, as he has been smart in leaving these deliveries but this time around, he swung his blade at this but luckily for him, there was no edge on this one.
Fuller and a little bit of shape away! It is stroked to mid off.
Outside off, not a lot of carry. It is left alone.
On off, SS is solid in his defensive push.
Good, quick run. A back of a length and around off, tapped to the leg side for a quick single. Good communication by both these batters.
Good length and on middle, Smith moves across to his off stump and flicks this to mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off again, Steven is not interested in having a piece of this.
A more traditional leave by Smith this time around as he raises his blade to this ball that was outside off on a length.
Length and outside off, left alone by Smith in his characteristic fashion.

Smith opens his account for the game. A length ball around off, Smith punches this one through the carpet, towards long off. Not enough on the shot to cross the ropes as the fielder cuts it off. Smith still completes three runs.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and around off, Smith pushes this to the mid on region. 'No runnn', says Smith, to Marnus, about the single.
Down the leg side, Steven misses his flick away.
Good shape from Thakur. On a length, starts at around off, nips away after taking the deck. Smith lets this one go to the keeper.
Steven Smith is the new batter in at Number 4. He would not have expected walking out so early in the game.

OUT! CAUGHT! And now, Harris falls and Australia lose both their openers very early on in the game. Thakur strikes right on the first ball of his spell. Thakur dishes a length ball on middle, Harris looks to clip this one to the leg side but he does so uppishly. Unluckily for him, there is a fielder present there at square leg. Sundar, there, judges it well and takes it nicely. Just the start that India would have wanted as they have sent both the Australian openers packing.
Shardul Thakur is introduced into the attack.
Outside off, left alone. A good over by Natarajan comes to an end. A maiden as well.

Good from Natarajan. Makes the batsman play at this. He bowls a length ball on middle and leg, Marnus looks to tuck this one away but he misses and the ball takes the pad and rolls to the leg side. Marnus looks for a single but he decides not to, in the end.
Outside off again, not played at.
Dishes a length delivery outside the off pole, ML raises his blade and leaves this one alone.
Another length delivery angling into the right-hander, Labuschagne looks to defend but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes towards the fielder at gully.
Outside off on a length, Marnus watchfully lets this one go to the keeper.
A single to end! This is a little too straight, it is worked down to fine leg for one.

The round the wicket angle almost does the trick! This is angled into the off pole, Harris is indecisive whether to leave it or play at it. He looks to leave it right at the end but it goes off the inside edge, past the off pole and down to fine leg for one.
Length and outside off, not a lot of carry this time to the keeper as it is left alone.
Back of a length this time and it is on off, Harris stands tall and defends it onto the ground.
Bangs it on a length this time and it is a lot closer to the off pole too. Angling away though so it is left alone.
Harris finally goes at one outside off, it is short and there to be hit. He though is beaten by the extra zip in the surface.
More closer to the off pole, this time. But still, ML does not want to have a poke at this and lets this one through to Pant.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length, around off, Marnus drives this one to the left of Natarajan, who does well to dive in that direction and stop the ball well.
Identical to the previous delivery, Marnus is not interested in having a poke at this. Patient play here, from Labuschagne.
On a length and outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one. 'Bowling Nat, Bowling Nattt', is the cry from the Indian players. They are trying their best to motivate the debutant.
Full length and on middle, clipped towards the fine leg region for a single by Marcus.
Good length and on middle, this is defended nicely.

FOUR! Short and put away! First boundary of the Test off the blade! Siraj goes for a surprise bumper! Labuschagne is not taken by surprise. He swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side and it races away. Not a bad idea by Siraj to go for the short one but Marnus was up for the challenge.
Excellent! This is on a length and around off, Labuschagne gets right behind the line and blocks it. Good line and length and a good defensive stroke as well.
Another one on the stumps, the length is a tad short. Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket easily.
Angled into the middle pole, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Good length and on off, it is defended solidly.
Another one well outside off, not played at. Harris is not tempted by the width Natarajan is offering. He needs to make the battter play a lot more.

Very well fielded! That made a cracking sound of the bat! It is on middle, Harris flicks it right off the middle towards mid on. Saini there dives to his left and stops it brilliantly. He is down on the ground for some time and then smiles and gives a thumbs up. All good then!
Outside off, wanting Harris to play a loose shot. He evades it.
Back of a length ball and on off, Harris stays back and defends it onto the ground.
Slightly closer to the off pole than the last ball, it is not played at.
Outside off, Harris shoulders arms to this one.
Fuller and on middle, Harris works it to mid on. Natarajan has overstepped again. He has probably not got his run up right as of yet. Two no balls in two overs.
Full length delivery around that fifth stump channel, Marnus lets this one through to the keeper.
Short of a length and around off, Labuschagne works this to the leg side. 'No runnn', says Marnus, regarding the single. A loud and clear no.
Outside off, no shot offered to this by Marnus.

FOUR LEG BYES. Siraj strays his line this time around. Bowls this one on a length and on the pads, Labuschagne looks for the tuck away but misses and the ball takes the pads, goes past the keeper, into the fine leg fence.
Another length delivery outside off, Marnus has no issues in leaving this one alone.
A good start to Siraj's second over. On a length, outside off, nips away after pitching. Labuschagne, though is not interested in playing at this one.
An away swinger to end! It is outside off though and not played at.
A solid defensive stroke! On middle, it is blocked nicely.
Gets this one to zip off the surface and also bounce a little bit extra! Length and around the pads. Harris looks to put bat on ball but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Goes back to bowling it outside off, left alone.
Makes the batter play! On a length and around middle, defended nicely.
Down the leg side this time, it is left alone. Natarajan has overstepped here so that is a no ball.
Good start by Natarajan! He gets this one to shape away and it is on a length outside off. Left alone. Natarajan has overstepped here so that is a no ball.

Early blow for Australia. They lose Warner very early in the innings. Who comes out now? Marnus Labuschagne is in at Number 3. Also, the debutant T Natarajan to bowl from the other end. What a moment this is for him.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! That is the ideal start for India! They strike in the first over and it is the big wicket of David Warner! His run of low scores continues. That is a superb nut though. He lands it on a length and around middle, gets it to angle away. Warner looks to defend but is done in by the angle. He ends up playing inside the line. It goes off the outside edge low between first and second slip. Rohit Sharma dives and takes a brilliant catch. A very good ball, a very good catch and a top wicket to end an excellent first over from Siraj, probably the leader of the attack in this Test sets the tone early on.
A loud and good call of no there from Warner! Length and around off, Warner pushes it towards cover. He takes off at first but then makes a loud and clear call of no.
Siraj goes full and wide again outside off, he is probably trying to get the ball back in but it is left alone.

Confident boosting shot from Harris to get off the mark! It is full and on a drivable length. Harris leans into it and strokes it through covers. The outfield is not the fastest and hence, the ball is tracked down. Three taken.
Lovely stuff! Got the last ball to come back in, this one is angled away. It is a length delivery and on off. Harris is beaten as he looks to defend inside the line.
Australia and Warner are underway! Some inward movement for Siraj! This starts on off and then comes back in. Warner looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for one.

Right then. We are done with all the pre-match formalities as the action is all set to begin. The players of India walk out and look to spread out to their respective positions out on the field. The openers for Australia, David Warner and Marcus Harris make their way out into the middle. Mohammed Siraj to begin proceedings with the ball for the visitors. Here he comes...
Time for the National Anthems! Both sets of players line up and first it will be the National Anthem of the visitors, which will be followed by the hosts'.
A guard of honor by the Australian team for Nathan Lyon as he makes his way out. He will be playing his 100th TEST!

India (Playing XI) - Rohit Sharma, Shubman Gill, Cheteshwar Pujara, Ajinkya Rahane (C), Mayank Agarwal (IN PLACE OF HANUMA VIHARI), Rishabh Pant (WK), Washington Sundar (IN PLACE OF RAVINDRA JADEJA), Shardul Thakur (IN PLACE OF JASPRIT BUMRAH), Navdeep Saini, Mohammed Siraj, T Natarajan (IN PLACE OF RAVICHANDRAN ASHWIN).

Australia (Playing XI) - David Warner, Marcus Harris (IN PLACE OF WILL PUCOVSKI), Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Matthew Wade, Cameron Green, Tim Paine (C/WK), Pat Cummins, Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood.

The skipper of India, Ajinkya Rahane, starts off by saying that they had to make some changes due to injuries but in the end, it is an opportunity for the others and that they are looking to do well. Talking about Natarajan and Sundar who are making their debut, he says that they have played in shorter formats and that he just wants them to enjoy this opportunity. States that Ashwin, Bumrah, Vihari and Jadeja miss out due to injury and they are replaced by Mayank, Thakur, Natarajan and Sundar. Feels that this rivalry is as good as India and Pakistan one and that this is a big series and they just want to do well and they do not want to think far too ahead.

The Australian skipper, Tim Paine says that it is good to be back out here in Brisbane and he is looking for some cricket. States he is happy to win the toss and bat first. Mentions the wicket looks a lot harder than it looks generally but it seems dry underneath and there is a crack right in the center which is quite surprising. Adds it is a great opportunity for Marcus Harris, as he has scored a lot of runs in the domestic circuit and he is eager to go.
TOSS - The men who matter, Tim Paine and Ajinkya Rahane are out in the middle for the all important toss. Up goes the coin and it lands in the favour of Australia. THEY WILL BAT FIRST!

The Aussies, would have probably thought they should have won the last game. The hosts should have had an unassailable lead heading into this one. That though is not the case. Despite not being at their best in the last two Tests, they would be very confident especially at the Gabba which is deemed as a fortress for them. A win is what they need to retain the trophy. So you can probably expect them to come out all guns blazing. Stay tuned for the toss in a bit...

Heading into the game, the Aussies are favorites once again especially against an Indian side which is going through injury issues. However, we have seen enough fight and determination from this Indian squad to actually believe they can still come out with a win. The fight shown in the last game would have surely lifted their spirits and the players will be rearing to go and will be hungry for a victory.
It is time for the 4th and final Test of this series. Brisbane is the venue and it is all to play for as the winner takes the series. Hello and welcome to the coverage.

Before the Aussie innings begins, Josh Hazlewood is caught for a quick chat. Tells that there are a few cracks but nothing much is happening for the bowlers. Says that their plan will be to see off the day and return on Day 4. Adds that he is pleased with his performance.

Right! Plenty of overs still left on Day 3. The Indians will look to close the day on a positive note here. The Aussie openers, on the other hand, would try and negotiate this testing phase. So, will the Indians be able to strike early or will the Aussies go to Day 4 unscathed? We will find out soon as the Aussie openers arrive to bat for their second innings.

Frustration kept creeping in for the Aussies as Sundar and Thakur kept going strong. They threw everything at the two but failed to get past their grit and determination. Eventually, Cummins found a way through as he removed Shardul but not before the Indians frustrated them quite a lot. Sundar continued for a while before Starc scalped him with a bouncer. In the end, the Aussies will be frustrated and tired as well. They had the chance to bundle the Indians and take a massive lead but they just couldn't do that in time as the Indians kept pushing them back. Eventually, Hazlewood removed the last wicket and ended up with a fifer.

What a terrific phase for the Indians in this final session of the day! Thakur and Shardul went bang, bang and brought up their maiden half tons. They carried on and added 123 before Thakur was removed by Cummins. Sundar continued and took India closer to the Aussie score. Starc got the better of Sundar eventually for 62. Siraj and Natarajan then faced the short ball music and added a few more vital runs. Indians were bowled out for 336, giving away the lead of 33 runs.

OUT! TIMBER! THERE IT IS! Siraj's small yet entertaining knock comes to an end. Hazlewood gets his 5th wicket of the innings and he has bowled really well. A length ball, around off, Siraj looks to smack this one away to the off side but he misses. The ball does not. Timber. INDIA GET BOWLED OUT FOR 336.
A length ball on off, Siraj walks across to the off side and looks to swing his blade across the line but he misses it.
Full toss on off, Siraj slices this one to deep point. Has the option of taking the single but decides not to.

FOUR! Well played by Siraj! Very cheekily done by Mohammed! A shortish length ball around off, Siraj sways away from the line and plays a ramp shot over the slip cordon and the ball crosses the ropes at the third man region.

An appeal for LBW but turned down. A full ball on middle and leg, Natarajan misses his attempt to block this one. The players appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Was going down the leg pole. Paine does not want to take the review as well.
Finally, connects bat to ball this time. Length and around off, Natarajan looks to play at this one but the ball takes the inside edge and goes onto hit him on the pads.
Short and down the leg side, Natarajan heaves a sigh of relief as he lets this one go through.
PLAY AND A MISS. Another one. Slightly short and around off, Natarajan looks to push this away to the off side but he gets beaten all ends up.
Short of a length on the body, Natarajan does well to fend it on the leg side.
BEATEN! A shortish and around off, Natarajan sways and looks to push this to the off side late but he does not connect.
Connects it well this time. Length and on off, Siraj lofts this one over the cover region and the batters come back for the second. India trail by 37 runs now.
SWING AND A MISS. On a shorter length and on middle, Siraj looks to pull this one away to the leg side but he does not connect bat with ball. Living dangerously, are these two.
Length and on off, slammed through the mid off region for a single. Could have taken two but Natarajan was happy to settle for the single. First run for Natarajan in Tests.
Another bumper on off, Natarajan looks to play at this but he misses and the ball goes to Paine, behind the sticks. He survives another one. How long can he stay out there for?
Full toss on off, Siraj moved to the leg side and so he had to reach out and work this to the deep point region for a single.
Length and outside off, Siraj walks across to the off side and looks to swing his blade towards the fine leg region but he misses. Looking to be aggressive, is Siraj.

OUCHHH! Starc welcomes Natarajan to International Test cricket. Bowls a short of a length ball on middle, Natarajan is not able to move away and gets hit on the body. India trail by 41 runs and they have only one wicket remaining.
T Natarajan is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one falls and it is also the big wicket of Washington Sundar! Paine's decision to bring back Starc has paid rich dividends. Starc dishes a back of a length delivery around off, Sundar leans away and looks to guide this one, opening up the face of his blade, down to the third man region. He does so uppishly and this one goes towards the gully region, where Green gets low and takes an excellent catch. A top, top knock from the youngster comes to a close.
Very full and on off, jammed out by Washington towards the mid off region.
Defends this one back towards Starc with a straight blade.
Down the leg side, WS misses his tuck away.

Great, great running by Sundar. Short of a length and outside off, slashed away to deep point. As soon as Sundar hit it, he realized that two was on and he runs hard and well to come back for the double.
Connects well again. Length, on off, punched through covers for a brace. India now trail by 43 runs.
FOUR! WOAH! That came out of nowhere! Siraj starts off with a boundary! Outside off on a good length, Siraj slashes this one over the backward point region and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
Mohammed Siraj is in at number 10.

OUT! CAUGHT! The short ball does the trick now for the Aussies! Hazlewood sends Saini packing and they really needed this wicket. Josh dishes a short of a length delivery around off, Saini, again looks to push this one away with a block, tries to defend with a straight blade. The ball though takes the outside edge and flies towards the slip region, where Steven Smith is as safe as house. India trail by 49 runs.
Short of a length and around off, Saini looks to block this one out but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes to the gully region.
Now, Navdeep decides to offer a solid defense to this length delivery around the off pole.

What's the field then? Short leg and leg gully in place. Two men in the slips. Green is waiting in the gully region and there is a man at third man too. The Aussies are not expecting Saini to go down the ground and he is getting peppered with short stuff too.
Bumper, on middle, Saini is happy to leave this one alone.

Sundar has got peppered in this over with short ball from Cummins. And the Indian physio is out in the middle. The umpires are standing pretty close too. They want to get on with the game quickly as well. Sundar doesn't take a lot of time.
Back of a length again, on leg, WS hops and looks to tuck this one to the leg side but he misses and the ball takes the pad and lobs up just ahead of the fielder at square leg.
Bouncer, down the leg side, left alone.

Ouch..right on the shoulder! A shortish length ball on off, Sundar looks to sway away from the line of the ball but the ball goes onto hit him on the shoulder. It lobs up and just bounces past the stumps. Sundar is as cool as a cucumber, even though that would have stung.
On off, length delivery, pushed to mid off.
Short of a length again, around off, Sundar looks to push this to the off side but the ball takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads.
Back of a length and around off, Navdeep sways away and then just guides it towards third man for a single. Gets off the strike.
Well left by Sundar. Another bouncer on middle, Sundar sways away from the line of the ball. Might have thought about playing a shot but made a good, smart choice to just let it be.
Goes on the back foot again, but instead of blocking it out, he decides to punch this one to the cover region but he finds Wade there, who stops this one well.
Now he backs away and defends this one back towards Josh.
Shortish length and around off, Washington taps this one late towards the slip cordon.
Now, the Aussies will try peppering the Indian tail with short balls. Hazlewood dishes a bouncer again. On middle. Sundar has no problems in sitting under this one.
Back of a length and around off, Sundar pushes this one to the cover region.
Josh Hazlewood is on now. 21-5-43-3 are his numbers so far.
The last ball is also a bumper. But it is down the leg side. Saini knows that he has to do. Just sits under this one and lets it through.
Outside off, left alone.
Another bouncer on off, Saini looks to fend this one away but the ball just zips past the outside edge and goes into Paine's mitts.
Short and outside off, left alone by Saini.
Another very sharp bouncer! Saini somehow manages to move out of the way.

FOUR! Lucky boundary, this. But the Indians do not care. A short one on middle, Saini looks to fend this one away but the ball takes the gloves and lobs over the slip cordon. The ball runs away to the third man ropes as the fielder gives it chase. India trail by 50 now.

DRINKS! What a phase for the Indians. They have reduced the deficit to just 54 runs. They have lost Shardul but Sundar is still out in the middle. The Indians will look to add as many as runs they could. The Aussies now will hope to wrap things up really quickly.
SIX! BOOM! What a strike from Sundar. Tossed up and around off and middle, Sundar slogs it way over wide long on for a biggie. It is the no-look shot from Sundar. Amazing hit.
Looks to paddle it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the body.
Another leave from Sundar as the ball pitches outside off and goes away.
Fuller but wide outside off, Sundar lets it be.
Short and wide again, Sundar cuts, finds cover.
Short and wide outside off, Sundar cuts it through point. Denies the single. Interesting.
Shortish and just outside off, Saini pokes at it. The ball takes the outside edge. Smith at second slip dives to his right to stop the ball.
Review time! A surprising review from Paine and Australia.

NOT OUT! Another review that has gone by for the Australians! Shorter and around off, Saini looks to sway away from the line of the ball and does so. Paine collects and appeals as he thinks that he has gloved this one. No says the umpire. Tim Paine is not convinced and he wants this checked upstairs. Hot Spot comes in first and shows nothing. The third umpire wants to check this again with Ultra Edge and the result is the same. No edge. Will remain not out and Australia just have one review remaining now.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Who is in next? Will it be Navdeep Saini? Yes, it is Saini.

OUT! BOWLED! Finally, finally, Australia get their breakthrough. They have been toiling hard so far and finally, Cummins comes along and disturbs the timber behind. It's not that they have not been trying to scalp the wicket, but it is just that these two were playing on another level so far. But, Cummins shows his class to break this stand. Pat fires in a length delivery around the off pole, jags back in after hitting the deck, Thakur swings his blade at this one looking to bang it away but he misses this one. The ball goes onto clip the top of the off stump. The 123-run stand comes to an end but what a partnership this has been. Thakur walks back but he should be very proud of the way that he has played. India are still 60 runs behind.

In the air...safe. Thakur does not lose his wicket here. Short and around off, Thakur swivel-pulls this one to the left of the deep square leg region. The fielder goes that way but the ball lands safe. Two taken.
Back of a length, around off, ST is solid in his defensive push.
Short and around off, WS rocks back and punches this one to the cover region. Labuschagne does well to dive and stop this one. 'NICE, MARNIEEEE', says Paine, praising his compatriat.
Loopy around off again, Washington plays this one to the short cover fielder.
Flighted around off, pushed to the cover region.
On middle, dug out back towards Nathan.
Outside off, Sundar, again leaves it alone.
Floated outside off, Sundar leaves this one alone. Paine collects and whips the bails off but Sundar's foot was always inside the crease.
Length, on off, clipped slightly uppish towards mid on but it falls short. A dot to end the over.
Short of a length and on the pads, Sundar hops and clips this one towards fine leg and rotates the strike. This partnership now moves onto 121 runs.
Length and around the off pole, Sundar shoulders arms to this one.
Slightly short and on off, Shardul hooks this one to the deep square leg region for a single.
Crisp shot but straight to the fielder. A fullish length ball on off, Thakur slams this one towards the mid off region but it is straight to the fielder there.
Short of a length and around off, tapped to the point region.

Loopy on off and middle, Sundar pushes it back towards Lyon, who inturn throws it just past Sundar, to Paine. Signs of frustation creeping in. Surely! 100 overs bowled by the Aussies in this innings. More than 33 overs faced by these two. This is some fightback.
LEG BYE. Floated around middle and leg, Thakur misses his flick and the ball takes the pads and rolls to the short fine leg region. A leg bye for the Indians.
On middle, Thakur is solid in his defense.
Flighted and around off, Shardul looks to block but the ball takes the outer half of the bat and goes towards the point region.
Gives it some air and lands it on middle, blocked out.
Floated on off, Thakur keeps this one out successfully.
Down the leg side, Thakur looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes towards square leg. A leg bye taken. 7 from the over.
FOUR! A boundary now! Cummins bangs it short and Shardul goes for the pull. Doesn't connect it that well but it is good enough to go to the fine leg fence, off the top edge.

Now he comes forward and looks to defend with a soft hands. The ball takes the otuer half this time and goes through backward point. Two taken before the fielder can get to the ball. 300 up for the visitors.
And again! This one is angled in a touch but he trusts the bounce and allows the ball to go over the off pole.
Short and wide outside off, Thakur, like a set top-order batsman says that I won't be throwing my bat that wide and shoulders arms.
Fullish and around off, defended.
Change in bowling. Pat Cummins is back on.

Two runs this time. 'Catch' was the call but this one drops short. Floated around off, Sundar chips this one over the cover region but luckily for him, the ball lands safe. The batters come back for the double.
Flatter and on middle, pushed through mid on for a single.
On off, worked to the leg side for one run.
Full and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Short ball on middle, Thakur pulls it down to deep mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
This one is wide outside off. Sundar moves out of the way.
Ouch! Nasty short ball from Starc. Sundar looks to work it on the leg side but it bounces a bit extra and hits him on the chest. Shows no pain, does the young man.
Fullish and around off, punched through mid off for a single.

HALF-CENTURY FOR SUNDAR! On Test debut, with the team losing the plot, a superb, superb inning from the debutant. He got in the team ahead of Kuldeep Yadav as a spinner, because he could bat, and boy he has repaid the trust the Indian management showed on him superbly. Gets there by pushing the fuller ball around off towards mid off and taking a quick single. The crowd here at the Gabba are on their feet. Sensational stuff.
Banged short but down the leg side. Sundar sits under it.
Shortish and on the pads, Thakur tucks it towards fine leg for one.
Flatter and around off, punched towards the cover region. 11 off the over.

FOUR! WOW! Was that right-handed Virat Kohli? Looked like that way. Fast hands from Sundar there. Lyon tosses it up and Sundar reaches out drills the drive through the covers. Sundar moves to 49 now. Also, 100-run stand is up too.
Short and wide, Sundar cuts but finds the point fielder.
Short and on middle, pulled down to deep square leg for one.
Looped up and around off, blocked.

SIX! FIFTY FOR SHARDUL! Maiden Test half-century for Shardul. What a knock, what a sensational knock it has been from the man playing only the 2nd Test of his career. What a way to get to the milestone. Lyon tosses it up and Thakur jumps out of his crease and powers it way over long on for a biggie. He started his innings with a biggie and it looked like he will just do the slogging here and try to throw the bat to find a few runs before eventually falling. However, once he got himself in, he just hung in and calmly played a few superb strokes to get to this milestone. How long can he continue now?
Back of a length and around off, punched towards the point region.
Down the leg side. Sundar looks to flick but misses.
Quick single. Length ball around off, Shardul pushes it to the right of the cover fielder. Calls for a run and gets it easily.
FOUR LEG BYES! Short ball on the body, Shardul looks to get out of the line of the ball but gets hit on the back. The ball then races to the fine leg fence.
Banged short and on middle, Shardul ducks.
Short but down the leg side. Thakur first though of clipping that on the leg side but withdrew his bat at the last moment.
Driven well but straight to the cover fielder. Lyon gives the ball air and bowls it wide too. Sundar nails the drive but straight to the mid off fielder.
Looped up and around off and middle, Thakur looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and goes towards short fine leg. They cross.
Looks to come down the track this time but Lyon smartly shortens the length. Shardul does well to bunt it down on the pitch.
On off, watchfully kept out.
Around off, Shardul comes forward and blocks.
Flat and around off, played back to the bowler.

Good tight over this one from Starc. This one pitches just outside off on a shortish length. Takes off a touch as Sundar does well to pull his bat out of the line of the ball. Paine does well to leap high and get a hand to it. Replays later on showed that Sundar had got some gloves on this one. So, a dropped chance from Paine.
Play and a miss! Full and just outside off, Sundar looks to drive but misses.
Back of a length and around off, Sundar moves out of the line.

EDGY FOUR! A length ball around off and middle, Sundar looks to work it on the leg side but gets a thick outside edge. The ball though goes between the second slip fielder and the gully fielder. The Aussie lead is under 100 now.
Back of a length and just around off, poked towards point.
Good bumper! It is around off and middle. Sundar sits under it.
On off, played back to the bowler.
Flatter and just around off, punched straight to the cover fielder.
Tossed up and around off, a solid front foot defense.
Flatter and just around off, stays back and blocks, does Shardul.
Tossed up and outside off, Thakur looks to defend but the ball bounces a touch and hits the handle of the bat.
Shortish and just outside off, cut towards point for a run.

FOUR! BOOM! What a shot! Shot of the day from Shardul. Length ball, wide outside off, Thakur thumps it through the covers and it races to the fence. One of the express Aussie pacers is getting spanked here.
Full and outside off, Shardul looks to drive but the ball takes the inner half and goes towards the bowler.
Lovely ball. Pitches just around off on a shortish length and leaves the right-hander. Thakur pokes at it but is beaten.
Fullish and around off, Sundar pushes it to the right side of the man at mid on. Calls for a quick run and completes it easily.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sundar hops and taps this one to the leg side.
Fuller and around off, Sundar drives it straight back to the bowler.
Loopy and just outside off, Shardul defends off his front foot. Lyon looking frustrated here.
Flat and just outside off, pushed to the left of the bowler.
Loopy ball around off, kept out.
Short and around off and middle, punched back to Lyon.
Flatter and just wide outside off, Sundar punches it wide of cover-point for one.
Floated around off, Sundar blocks.
Full and wide outside off, Shardul goes for the drive again. This time he ends up hitting it slightly off the outer half of the bat towards point. 8 off the over.
A solid front foot defense this time as Starc bowls a length ball around off.
Starc gets back to bowling the length ball just outside off, Shardul lets it go.
FOUR! Slashed away! Short and wide outside off, Thakur slams it over backward point and finds the fence. Terrific stuff. Second boundary in the over and Shardul is into the 40s.
Goes full again and bowls this one wide outside off, Thakur lets it go.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! What a way to welcome the pacer in this new session. Fullish and outside off, Thakur leans into the shot and drives it through mid off. It races away to the fence.
Who partners Lyon with the cherry? It will be Mitchell Starc. 16-2-65-1 are his figures so far.
Floated on middle, blocked on the off side. A maiden to start from Lyon.
Looped up and on middle, blocked.
Tossed up and on middle, blocked out off the front foot.
Loopy delivery around off, Sundar taps this one to the off side.
Flighted outside off, Sundar drives it well but the fielder at covers makes a good stop.
Floated outside off, Sundar watchfully lets that one through to the keeper.

Right then. We are back for the final session of Day 3. The batters for India, Washington Sundar and Shardul Thakur make their way out into the middle. The Aussies also come out and spread to their respective positions on the field. Spin to start off the final session of the Day as Nathan Lyon is handed the ball. Let's begin...
... DAY 3, SESSION 3 ...

Right! This sets up a fine final session of the moving day of the Test match. India will feel that they have done superbly well to hang in there and wipe out the deficit quite spectacularly. The Aussies will be frustrated. They will return for the final session with different plans. Join us for the same in a short while.

It was Hazlewood who once again did the trick with the ball for the Aussies. He got the better of Agarwal first and then got the big wicket of good-looking Pant as well. They would've thought that they have got the opening now to roll over the inexperienced lower order of the Indians. However, they were denied any sort of real chance by Sundar and Shardul.

The session started with Agarwal throwing his wicket away on the 2nd ball post Lunch. Pant followed him soon after playing a couple of gorgeous strokes. Thakur arrived and played a few aggressive shots and along with debutant, Sundar combined for a fine partnership. Both were tested by short stuff from the Aussies but they hung in there and played their shots once the opportunity came. They have added vital 67 runs between them already.

Another fine session, maybe this one has gone to the visitors. With the last two recognized batters back to the pavilion in the first hour of the session, the Aussies smelled blood. However, the stand between Sundar and Thakur means that India have reduced the lead by quite a bit. And the good thing for the visitors is that both of them are still out in the middle.
Back of a length and around off, Thakur offers a solid block to this and he negotiates the final delivery before the Tea break. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Another length delivery outside off, Thakur is well aware off his off stump as he raises his blade and lets this one through to Paine.
Bumper on middle and leg, Thakur sits under this one well.
Outside off, Thakur leaves it alone.

FOUR! Back-to-back boudaries for Shardul! On a length and around off, Thakur looks to push this one to the off side but the ball takes the outer half of the blade and it goes through the gully region into the third man fence. Also, brings up the 250 for the Indians. This partnership moves onto 67 runs.

FOUR! Thakur starts the over off with a boundary! A very good shot! Fullish length and around off, Thakur drives this one past the bowler, through mid on for a boundary. He has played some really good shots so far.
Gentle push for a single. Around off, good length, Washington plays this one towards covers for one. 5 runs off this over.
Short of a length and around off, Thakur hops and pushes this one towards the mid on region.
Three this time. Full and on the pads, clipped through square leg. The ball is chased by the fielder and the batters collect three by the time he collects and throws it back.
Length and around the off pole, Sundar shoulders arms to this one.

The Indian physio is out in the middle. For the umpteenth time in this series. He is here this time to check the finger of Shardul. Looks like there is some swelling there. Nitin Patel, the Indian physio, has done his job here and Shardul is ready again. And the good news for the visitors is that Saini is padded up.

Short of a good length delivery around middle and leg, Thakur looks to tuck this one but the ball takes the gloves and goes to the leg side. The batters take a single. That would have stung. Getting hit flush on the gloves.
Solid defense offered by Thakur to this good length delivery around the off pole.
Good length and around off, Sundar pushes this to the point region. Maiden by Cummins.
Nasty bouncer, this! It is around middle and leg, Sundar ducks under this one well to let it through to Paine.
Similar delivery as the last ball, pushed to the cover-point region.
Play and a miss! Another length delivery, around off, Sundar looks to have a push at this but he misses it altogether.
Good length and around off, Sundar works this to the fielder at mid off.
Back of a length and around off, tapped to the off side.
Play and a miss! Length ball outside off, Shardul throws his bat at it but makes no connection.

Huge appeal but turned down! Was it doing too much? Maybe some bat too. That's what Paine felt and didn't go for the review. Fullish and around middle and leg, Shardul looks to flick but misses. He gets pined on the pad. A loud, loud appeal but turned down. No review from the Aussies.
Fuller and around off, Shardul is solid in defense again.
Banged short but it is down the leg side. Shardul sits under it.
Full and around off and middle, stroked straight to mid on.
Good length and around off and middle again, pushed towards mid on.
Good length and around off, pushed towards mid off. Josh has overstepped. No Ball.
Length ball just outside off, Sundar comes forward and pushes it towards mid off.
Shortish and around off, poked on the off side for nothing.
Landed around off and middle, played back to the bowler.
Shortish and down the leg side, Sundar looks to clip it on the leg side but misses.

FOUR! Shot! What a solid punch! 50-run stand is up between the two. Shortish and just outside off, Sundar punches it on the up and finds the gap between point and gully. Fine stroke and Sundar moves to 35.
Length ball around off, poked towards gully where the fielder dives to stop the ball on his left.
Good length and on middle, blocked out.

EDGED AND FOUR! Thakur had no idea how to play at that but he will take it. A length ball around off, it comes back in sharply. Shardul looks to defend but he gets an inside edge. The ball goes over the stumps. Paine behind the sticks, dives to his left and tries to catch but the ball evades his dive and races to the fine leg fence. The stand moves to 49. Vital, vital runs for the Indians.
FOUR. Good batting by Thakur. Gets another boundary. Moves onto 19 from 43 balls too. A back of a length ball on middle and leg, Thakur tickles this one to the fine leg region for a boundary.
That's a jaffa! Length and around off, Shardul looks for the poke but he misses the ball completely.
Another one in the channel but Thakur has grown in confidence. He covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Here's Josh Hazlewood now. 18-5-29-3 so far.
Length ball but wide outside off, left alone.
Bumper around off, Sundar sways away from the line of the ball.
Length and around off, WS pushes this one to the mid on region.
Full and around off and middle, Sundar forces it down the ground. Starc at mid on does well to stop the ball with a tumble to his right.
Misfield and runs. A back of a length delivery again, but this time, it is around off, Sundar punches this one through the mid off region where the fielder fumbles. Two runs.
Slightly behind the good length and on middle, flicked to the short leg fielder this time.
Back of a length delivery around middle, Sundar hops and tucks this one to the leg side.
The second new ball is available now! Time Paine has asked for it straightaway. Here's Pat Cummins to have a crack at the Indians with it first up.
Lands it around off on a full length, Thakur goes on his back foot and keeps this one out.
On off, blocked.
Loopy around off, Sundar gets forward and works this to the right of mid off. Picks up a single.
Short and around off again, Sundar rocks back and punches this one but he finds the fielder at cover-point.
Short and around off, pushed to the off side.
Floated around off, kept out.
Flatter and outside off, pushed towards point.
Low full toss, Thakur hits it hard but straight to the mid off fielder.
On off, pushed towards point.
Play and a miss! Some turn for Marnus there. Lands it shortish and around off, it spins away and beats the defensive poke of Shardul.
Short and just outside off, Thakur punches it towards point.
Very full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
The second new ball is just 12 balls away. So, Paine tosses the ball to Marnus Labuschagne.
A maiden from Lyon as Sundar bunts the last ball of the over by taking a big stride forward.
Looped up and outside off, driven towards the cover fielder.
Shortish and just around off, Sundar looks to cut but there isn't much room. Ends up mistiming it towards the cover fielder.
Tossed up again, Sundar is sound in defense off his front foot again.
Floated around off, Sundar comes forward to block.
Loopy ball around middle, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Banged short and on middle. Shardul ducks under it easily.
Fuller and around off, it is pushed towards mid on for a quick single.
Back of a length and around off, played back to Starc.
Short but way down the leg side. Left alone.
Short and on middle, Thakur plays a controlled pull down to deep square leg for a single.
Full and on the pads, Sundar whips it through square leg and gets three more before the fielder can get to the ball.
Thakur stays back and blocks the last ball of the over.
Sundar this time flicks the fuller ball one wide of the man at mid on for one.
Full and around middle and leg, kept out.
Flatter and just outside off, punched well but straight to the cover fielder.
Looped up and around off, a solid front foot block.
Tossed up and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Angled in from middle, Shardul looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad.

In the air... safe! Short and wide outside off, Thakur upper cuts it. Fails to get the timing all that well. It goes high in the air but drops safely as Green makes a good ground from gully, running back to catch but he fails to get there.
Short again, Sundar tucks it through square leg for one.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point off his back foot.
Starc bends his back and bangs it short. It is on middle and leg. Sundar sits under it.
Shortish and outside off, left alone.

DRINKS! Another battling hour of cricket! India lost Agarwal in the first over post Lunch and Pant joined him back in the pavilion soon, after playing a couple of good shots. After that, Shardul and Sundar too have taken the aggressive route and have found a few boundaries. Australia would feel that they are pretty close to bundling the visitors and taking a big lead. The Indians though will hope that these two add as many as possible to keep the deficit down. An interesting hour of play coming your way.
Flatter and around off, Thakur stays back to block.
Short and around off, Thakur pushes this one to the off side.
On off, kept out.
Flatter and around off, Thakur moves to the leg stump and punches this one towards the mid off region. Thinks about the single but they do not go for it, in the end.
Comes down the track slightly but Thakur tucks this one to the leg side, near the short leg fielder.
Floated on off, Shardul pushes it back towards Lyon.
Down the leg side, Sundar misses his flick. Productive over for the visitors. 10 runs off this over.
Short of a length and around off, WS hops and keeps this one out.

FOUR! Oh wow...Wonderful shot! Treat to the eyes. Full and around off, Sundar punches this one with a straight bat through the mid off region and the ball speeds away to the ropes. Back-to-back boundaries for Washington.
FOUR! Well played! Sundar is playing some good strokes! On a length on middle and leg, Sundar clips this one through the square leg region for a boundary.
Slightly behind the good length and around off, tapped through the gully region. Green gives it chase and stops it but not before the batters come back for the second run.
Outside off, good length, Washington shoulders arms to this one.
Loopy on off, pushed to the cover region.
EDGY. Floated around off, Shardul look to have a poke of this one but the ball takes the outside edge and falls just beside the slip fielder there.
Now prods forward and blocks this one out well. Thakur is on 12 from 18 balls.
On middle, tucked to short leg.
Floated outside off, Thakur looks to have a feel of this but he misses it.
Short and around off, nudged to the square leg region.
Good length and around off, tapped to the mid off region. Just the boundary off Starc's over.
Good shot but for no runs. Length, around off, punched to the cover region but straight to the fielder stationed there.
On off, guided to the gully region.
Length, outside off, Sundar leaves it alone.
On off, punched to the cover region.

EDGED....FOUR! Sundar survives. Another boundary which goes in the gap between the slip cordon and the gully region. A back of a length delivery outside off, Sundar swings his blade at this but the ball takes the outside edge, flies in between the gap, to the third man region for a boundary.
Change from the other end as well. Here's Mitchell Starc again. 12-2-43-1 from him so far.
On off, flat delivery, back foot defense is solid by Shardul. A maiden by Lyon.
Outside off again, Thakur shuffles across the off stump but offers no shot to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish, around off, Thakur goes on his back foot and defends this one back towards Nathan.
Floated around off, driven to the cover region.
Shortish and outside off, Thakur looks to cut this one away but he misses the ball completely.
Nathan Lyon returns. 13-2-28-1 are his numbers so far.
On middle, well kept out to the leg side.
PLAY AND A MISS! Ohhh...could have got the outside edge! A length delivery, outside off, Sundar swings his blade at this, looking to have a feel of this but he gets beaten.
Bumper on middle and leg, WS leaves it be.

A couple this time around. Around off, Sundar looks to push this one away to the off side but the ball takes the bottom edge and goes through the slip cordon. The batters get two runs. Also, 200 up for the visitors. India now trail by 168 runs.
Takes the edge. A back of a length delivery around off, Sundar looks to play at this but the ball takes the inside edge and hits him on the pads and then rolls to the off side.
Shorter and outside off, Washington leans away from the line of the ball.
On the pads, Thakur looks to tuck it away but he misses and it comes off his pads to the leg side. A good over for the Indians. 12 runs off this one.
Back of a length and around off, Shardul hops and blocks this one out.
He is going to get these short stuffs. Knowing that, maybe should've had got the arm guard there.

FOUR! What a glorious strike. A cover drive which might make Virat Kohli feel some complex. Beautiful. Length and around off, Thakur creams this one through the wide mid off region and the ball runs away to the ropes.
Short and on middle, ST ducks under this one. Has a wry smile after this, does Thakur.
More runs for Thakur. Back of a length and around off, Shardul hops and slams this one through the cover region and he picks up a brace.
SIX! TAKE THAT! Thakur takes it on and takes it on well! Goes all the way for a biggie! Shortish and on the body, Shardul swivel-pulls this one over the fence at fine leg for a biggie.
Shortish and around off, Sundar blocks this one out. A very good over for Josh and the Aussies.

LEG BYE. An appeal for LBW but turned down. A back of a length ball on middle and leg, Thakur looks for the tuck away but he misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but no says the umpire. The batters sneak in a leg bye. Probably was going down the leg side.
Length and around off, well kept out.
Shardul Thakur is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! An unbelievable reaction catch from Green and Pant's charge has been brought to a halt. The ball was traveling quickly and Green does extremely well to hold onto this. On the shorter side outside off, Pant leans away and looks to cut this one through the point region. He plays it late and it goes towards Green at gully, who pulls off an amazing catch to send Pant back to the pavilion. His short but good stay out in the middle has unfortunately come to an end. India slowly losing the plot here. They lose their 6th wicket now and the Aussies are smelling blood now.
Offers a solid defense this time around, does Rishabh.
Length and around off, driven through the carpet, towards deep covers for a couple of runs.
Bangs it short for Sundar. It is around off, Sundar moves out of the line of the ball. 9 off the over.
In the air... safe! A short ball around off, Pant looks to take it on but he fails to connect. It goes off the top edge but drops away from the short leg fielder. They cross for a run.
FOUR! TAKE THAT! Stunning from Pant. Full ball around off, Pant creams it through mid off. The fielder from the ring gives it a chase but fails to stop it.
Fuller and around off, pushed to mid off.
Fuller and wider, going away. Pant lets it be.

FOUR! Fine shot! Little wide and outside off, Pant rocks back and crunches it through backward point. Lyon, races across from his right and dives to attempt to stop the boundary but he is not able to and the ball touches the ropes. A good start to the over.
Bumper on middle and leg, Sundar ducks under it.
Length and around off, poked towards point this time.
Wide outside off, Sundar lets it be again.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Short and just outside off, Pant plays a controlled pull for a run towards deep mid-wicket.
Around off on a length, blocked out.
Short of a length and around off, tapped to the gully region.
Well punched but straight to short cover. On a length, around off, Sundar punches this one but it finds the fielder at covers.

Shot! Full and wide outside off, Pant nails the drive through the covers. The man from deep point runs to his left and does well to flick the ball in. The mid-wicket fielder returns the ball to the keeper. By that time, the batters take three.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Fuller and around off, blocked.
Shortish and just around off, Pant punches it through point. The deep point fielder runs to his right and stop the ball near the fence. Two taken.
Landed on a length and around off, Sundar offers a solid defense.
Banged short but down the leg side. Sundar sits under it.
Hazlewood comes 'round the wicket and bowls a length ball outside off, Sundar lets it go to the keeper.
Bangs it short and just around off, Sundar lets it go to the keeper.
Slightly short and around off, punched off the back foot.

FOUR! SHOT! First boundary in Test match cricket for Sundar. A superb shot through mid off. A fullish ball just outside off, Sundar gets on the front foot and strokes it through mid off for a boundary. That will give complex to any of the top order batter in the world.
Back of a length and on the ribs, Sundar clips it past the man at short leg. They take one. Pant wants the second but Sundar is not keen.
Good bumper and equally well left by Sundar.
Angled in from around off, Sundar blocks solidly again.
Landed around off on a length, Sundar is solid in his defense.
Fullish and around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Who will bowl from the other end for the Aussies? Pat Cummins, it is. 14-4-37-1 are his numbers so far.

What happened there? A blow on the body for the debutant. Hazlewood bangs it short again and it is around off, Sundar takes his eyes off and looks to evade the ball but it hits his shoulder. The ball flies towards Wade at the slip cordon. He dives forward and looks to catch but it falls well short. Bounces and then hits him on the head. A superb first over from Josh.
Shortish and outside off, punched through point for one.
Sundar is off and running in Test match cricket. A length ball around off, he tucks it through mid-wicket for one.
A bouncer to welcome the debutant. Sundar sits under it as it is slightly down the leg side.
The debutant, Washington Sundar is the new batter in.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Hazlewood is the man again. Poor, poor shot from Agarwal in the first over post Lunch. That was way too wide and outside off, he could've easily let that go to the keeper. Instead, he goes for that big booming drive. Throws the bat at it but it takes the outside edge and goes very quickly to Steven Smith at second slip. Smith does well to get both hands to it but it pops out. However, Smith keeps his eyes on the ball and grabs it on the second attempt. A fine knock from Agarwal but he has thrown it away.
Right on the money is Hazlewood. A length ball around off, Agarwal stays back to block it on the off side.

We are back for the second session on this moving day of the Test match. Mayank Agarwal and Rishabh Pant are the two Indian batters. The Aussies have taken their positions on the field. Josh Hazlewood to start off. Here we go...
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

Right! That marks a fine session of play. We are in for another intriguing phase of play when we return for the second session. India will hope that Agarwal and Pant combine for a big partnership.  Australia, on the other hand, would know that another wicket here and then they will have the chance of knocking the Indian tail rather quickly. How will things pan out in the afternoon session? We will soon find out. Join us back in a short while.

The Aussies kept things nice and cool in the first hour. Starc managed to induce a couple of outside edges of the Indian skipper but they didn't find the fielders. It was Hazlewood who got the big wicket of Pujara with a superb ball. After that, Rahane and Agarwal did well and were looking good. Starc returned and eventually managed the big scalp of Rahane, bowling that fuller ball outside off.

The Indians started the day nicely with Pujara and Rahane negotiating the initial burst from the Aussie quicks. It looked like Pujara will get set for the day but he was removed by a beauty from Hazlewood. However, after that, Rahane along with Agarwal did well to first get themselves in and then play a few fine strokes. They were looking set to make sure they remain unbeaten till the Lunch break but Starc got better of Rahane to make sure the game stays in balance. Agarwal has shown good form, batting at number 5 and the Indians will hope that he continues the way he has done so far.

A superb session of cricket! Good battle between bat and ball in this long session. With India adding 99 runs in the session and the Aussies getting the huge wickets of Pujara and Rahane means the session is nothing but shared by both sides.
Floated on middle and leg, Pant looks to flick this one to the leg side but he misses and gets hit on the pads. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Loopy on off, Pant keeps this one out.
Short and around off, Pant rocks on his back foot and cuts it through point to pick up a couple.
Flighted on off, Pant defends this one out. 'BOWLEDDDD, NATHAN', says Paine, from behind the stumps as he looks to cheer his bowler on.
Floated around off, Pant comes on his front foot and blocks this one out.
Floated outside off, Pant leaves it alone.
Outside off again, well left again by Mayank.
On off, pushed to covers.
Closer to the off pole, outside off, MA has no problems in leaving this one alone.

FOUR! BEAUTYYYY! What a shot, this is! Mayank is looking really good out there in the middle. Starc goes fuller and slightly straigter around off and middle, Agarwal punches this one past the bowler, through mid on and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
Outside off, well left by Mayank.
Short and on the body, Pant fends this one out to the leg side. The batters scamper through for the single.
Prods forward to block this one out now.
Short and around leg again, tucked to the fielder at short leg again.
Flat and around leg, tucked to short leg.
Short and around leg, tucked to the leg side.

SIX! That's a big, big six! That's how Agarwal likes to play, he likes to back himself. Floated around off, Agarwal skips down the track and powers this one over the long on fence for a biggie. 150 up for the Indians as well.
Pant gets off the mark. Flatter and around off, tapped to the point region for a quick single.
Outside off again, left alone again by Mayank.
Outside off, length, Agarwal offers no shot to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
Good, quick running. Back of a length and on middle, tucked to the square leg region. They take one and Mayank insists on the second. They come back for the second too.
Length and outside off, Mayank lets it be.
Way outside the off pole, left alone by Agarwal.
Full and around middle and leg, Pant keeps it out again.
Fuller and around middle, kept out.
Floated outside off, Pant lets it be.
Full and around off, Pant drives it back to the bowler. Lyon collects to his right.
Tossed up and outside off, driven wide of the man at mid off for one.
Flatter and around off, played back to the bowler.
Rishabh Pant is the new batter in. He was really good in the previous game. Can he continue his good form into this Test as well?

OUT! TAKEN! Rahane falls! Starc gets the breakthrough. It is the huge wicket of the Indian skipper. Full and wide outside off, Rahane goes for the drive again. He has edged a couple of times before but both the times the ball went through the gap between third slip and gully. This time, the ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to Wade who is at the third slip position. The Aussies have worked out their plan as Wade is bit closer to the gully fielder this time. And he is not going to miss out on this chance. Both the overnight batters for India have been dismissed now.
In the channel and angling away. Rahane shoulders arms.
Fullish and on the pads, flicked to deep mid-wicket for an easy single.
Short of a length but again wide outside off. Agarwal is not keen at playing at these.
Full again and wide again, left alone.
Fuller ball outside off, Mayank lets it go to the keeper.
Flat and on middle, Rahane goes back to work it towards square leg.
Dropped short and Mayank pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Loopy again, Agarwal flicks it towards mid-wicket again.
Looped up and around middle, kept out towards mid-wicket this time by Agarwal.
Flatter and around off and middle, worked towards short fine leg.
Shortish and around off, pushed down to long on for one.
Nathan Lyon is back on.

FOUR! Agarwal ends the over well for the Indians! Goes for a back of a length delivery around middle and leg, Agarwal just tickles this one to the fine leg region and the ball reaches the advertising triangles before the fielder can reach and stop it. Just the boundary off this over.
Starc dishes a bumper on middle, Agarwal does well to sway away from the line of the ball.
Another length delivery outside off, Agarwal is not tempted into driving this one and he lets it through to Paine.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off.
Starc starts with a fuller ball outside off, Agarwal lets it be.
Mitchell Starc is back on. 8-2-31-0 are his figures so far.
Back of a length and around off, poked towards point.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Banged short and on middle and leg, Mayank looks to pull. Doesn't connect it well but it goes to fine leg. A single taken.
Landed around off on a length, defended.
Full and on middle, it is flicked through square leg for a single.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
In the channel just outside off, comes back in nicely but Agarwal covers his stumps and makes a leave.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.
Length and around off, pushed to mid off.

EDGED AND FOUR! Full and wide outside off, Agarwal is lured into playing the big-booming drive away from his body. He goes hard at it but ends up getting it off the outside edge. This time the ball zips between second slip and gully and races away to the third man fence.
Landed around off on a length, blocked.
Edgy! A length ball around off, Rahane looks to defend but it takes the inner half and goes towards the leg side. They cross.
Fuller and outside off, Agarwal looks to drive but it goes off the inner half, back to the bowler.
Landed on a length and on middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.
A couple for Agarwal as he gently forces the fuller ball through mid on.
Banged short on middle and leg, Agarwal sits under it.
On off, pushed to the cover region.
Length and on middle, clipped to the leg side for a single.
On off, pushed to point.

NOT OUT! Australia lose a review and Mayank does not have to walk back. A back of a length delivery around middle and leg, Agarwal hops and looks to tuck this one away to the leg side. To the naked eye, it looks to have missed the bat and gone to the keeper. Paine collects and appeal though. No says the umpire. Tim Paine does not hesitate as the signals the 'T' symbol. Hot Spot comes in and it does not look like there was any bat on this. The third umpire wants Ultra Edge to confirm the same and it does. Came off the thigh pad. Will remain not out.

Review time! Australia have gone for a catch down the leg side. Paine is really confident as he calls for the 'T' quickly. There was some noise too. Here comes the replay. Nothing on the Hot Spot. The noise came from the ball hitting the thigh pad. And the onfield decision will stay. Australia lose one of their 3 reviews.
Another bouncer on middle and leg, Agarwal has no intention of playing at this. Just ducks under this one.
Shorter and on middle, Mayank ducks under this one well.
On off, blocked out.
Angles in a length delivery around off, goes just past the off pole, as Agarwal leaves it alone.
Good length and outside off, well left by Rahane.
On off, played to point.
Length and outside off, Ajinkya pushes this one towards point. Lyon, there dives to his left and stops the ball. Good work from the GOAT, out on the field.
On the pads, tucked through the square leg region for one run.
Full and around off, Mayank digs this one out towards covers.
Short of a length delivery and around off, Agarwal defends this one out with a straight bat.
The Indian captain is solid in blocking this one out. Also, a loud and clear 'no' for the single. 3 runs off this over by Cummins.
Good shot but for just a single. Length, around off, punched by Mayank towards covers where Labuschagne chases and makes a stop to keep this down to just a single.
Length again and around that 5th stump line, Agarwal is confident in leaving this one alone.
Outside off, length, left alone.
BEATEN. Lovelyyy! Lands in on a length and around off, nips away slightly, Agarwal looks to block this one out but the ball zips past the outside edge, into Paine's mitts.
Good length and around off, Mayank offers just a gentle push through the cover region to pick up a brace. Moves into the double digits with these runs, does Agarwal.
Pat Cummins is back. 11-3-29-1 from him so far.
Another length delivery outside off, no shot offered by Ajinkya.
Outside off, left alone by Jinks.

In the air...safe! On a length and around off, Rahane looks to play this to the off side but does so uppishly. But luckily for him, it lands short of the fielder there. Probably the lack of timing on this stroke saved the Indian skipper.
Outside off, let through to the keeper.

Well played by Agarwal. A full this this time, around middle, Mayank drives this one through mid on and Wade gives it chase. He wins the race and stops the ball before the ropes. But not before the batters come back for the third run. He will want to make a statement with his batting today.
Short of a length and around off, dabbed towards the off side.
Good length and around off, blocked out.
Josh makes Rahane play at this one as he bowls a shorter one on middle, it is pulled wide of deep square leg and the batters come back for the second run.
Slightly fuller but still outside the off pole. Ajinkya copies what he did on the previous delivery. Lets it be.
Characteristic leave by Rahane as he raises his blade to let this one through to Paine.
Short of a length and around off, Rahane blocks this one out well.
Length and around off, Rahane pushes this one to the mid on region.
Another leave by Mayank as this ball was outside off. Green starts off his spell with a maiden over.
Outside off, left alone.
Gets on the front foot and blocks this one out solidly.
Same delivery as the last ball, same shot offered by Agarwal too. Which is basically no shot.
Another length delivery, but slightly wider than the last one. Either ways, Agarwal does not want to have a bite of this cherry.
Here's Cameron Green to start the proceedings after the mini-break.
Green starts off with a length delivery outside off, Mayank shoulders arms to this one.

DRINKS. It was looking like India's phase but Hazlewood with the magic delivery sent Pujara packing. He was settling in for the day but Australia have got him just in time. Now, India will have to re-build again. Skipper Rahane has looked a bit tentative outside the off stump and he has survived a couple of close scares. He along with Agarwal will look to put on another good partnership. The Aussies, on the other hand, would fancy a wicket of two more before the Lunch break. We will find out how things pan out after this mini-break.
Full and around off and middle, Rahane looks to flick but it takes the outer half and goes towards the cover fielder.
Good bumper just outside off, Rahane sways away from the line.
Full and around off, Rahane flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace again.
Back of a length ball around off, Rahane gets on his toes to block it on the off side.
Landed around off on a good length, defended again, solidly.
Length ball around off, blocked.
Tossed up but wide outside off, left alone by Mayank this time.

FOUR RUNNING RUNS! Good from the Indians. A fuller ball outside off, Agarwal creams it through the covers. The point fielder gives it a chase and just before the ropes, manages to flick the ball inside the play. However, by the time he returns to pick and throw it to the keeper, the batters run 4.
Floated full and around off, Rahane flicks it hard towards mid on and takes a quick run.
Very full and around middle, played back to the bowler.
Shortish and on middle, Agarwal pulls it towards deep square leg for a single to get off the mark.
Flat and around off, Mayank comes on the front foot to block.
Angles in a good length delivery around off, Ajinkya keeps this one out.
Outside off, left alone by the Indian skipper.
Drags his length back this time and bowls a shortish delivery around off, Jinks takes it on and hooks this one towards square leg and collects a brace.
Offers a solid defense this time around, does Rahane.
BEATEN! Another gem of a delivery! A good length delivery around off, Rahane looks for the block but gets beaten all ends up.
Back of a length and around off and middle, Rahane looks to work this one to the leg side but he misses and gets hit high on the pads.
On off again, Mayank is solid in his blocking.
On off, Mayank works it back to the bowler.
Lovely shot but it will not reach the ropes. Slightly shorter again outside off, Rahane camps back and slashes this one through point. Takes three as the fielder cleans up in the deep.
Flatter and around off, Jinks backs away and blocks this one out.
Short and around leg, nudged around the corner to the square leg region.
Flatter around off, Rahane works this to the leg side.
Back of a length and around middle, Agarwal fends this one out towards the leg side. A good over for the Aussies. A maiden wicket over for Hazlewood.
Mayank Agarwal, the man who opened for India in the first 2 Tests, is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time, Hazlewood gets the edge and this will be the end of Pujara. A good, healthy edge and a very comfortable catch for the skipper. He goes back after scoring 25 runs. Josh bowls this on a length around the off pole, straightens a touch after hitting the deck. Pujara is lured into the defensive push and gets his bat ahead. The ball kisses the outside edge and goes towards Paine who takes a good catch. Pujara was looking set with the way he was playing, but Hazlewood sends him packing. Big, big wicket for Australia.
Short and outside off, Pujara is not interested in playing at this.
Length and around off, Pujara is solid in his defense.
On off, guided to the gully fielder.

IN THE AIR...SAFE! Pujara survives this scare. Hazlewood bangs this one short and around off, Pujara looks to sway away from the line but gets in a clumsy position. The ball takes the gloves, and then takes the bat and lobs ahead of the gully fielder, who runs forward quickly but the ball lands safely before he can scalp this one.
On off, well kept out. 7 off Lyon's first over.
FOUR! Good attacking intent shown from Ajinkya! Short and around off, Rahane backs away and slams this one through cover-point to find the ropes.
Floated around off, Rahane prods forward and blocks this one out towards point.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.

Three now. Flighted and around middle, Pujara, once again, skips down the track and clips this one behind square on the leg side. Cummins gives it chase and stops it before the ropes. The batters still manage to pick up three runs. 100 up for the Indians.
Floated around off, Pujara comes down the track a touch and pushes this to the mid on region.
Change from the other end as well. Time for spin on Day 3. Here's the GOAT. Three shy of 400 Test wickets.
Another length delivery, around off again, Rahane prods forward nicely and blocks this one out towards cover-point. A good start by Josh, with the cherry.
Good length delivery and around off, Jinks pushes this towards point. Is also quick to deny the single, on this occasion.
Good length and around off, Ajinkya pushes this one back to the bowler.
Quick run. Length and around off, Cheteshwar pushes this one to the point region. 'YEAH, YEAH', says Pujara. His compatriat, Rahane responds and they complete the run.
Pujara is solid this time as he defends this good length delivery around off towards the cover region.

Beaten! What a start by Hazlewood! Bowls it on a length around off, straigtens a touch after taking the deck, Pujara looks to have a tentative block at this but misses and the ball zips past his outside edge.
First change of the morning. Here's Josh Hazlewood with the ball. Kept things really tight on Day 2. What has he got here?
Nicely driven! Full ball around off, Pujara forces the drive through mid off. Wade gives it chase. Stops it near the fence but Pujara gets three more.
Short and wide outside off, Pujara looks to cut but ends up doing so off the bottom edge. It goes towards the cover region.
Outside off again, Pujara lets it go to the keeper again.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off.
Full and around off, Pujara drives it well but finds mid off.
Fullish but outside off, Pujara is not interested.
Banged short and Pujara lets it go. Paine leaps high to collect. Manages to make a half stop. A bye taken as the ball goes to short fine leg.
Full and around off, kept out.
Angled in from middle and leg, Pujara looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Nicely punched! A length ball just outside off, Rahane gets on his toes and punches it on the up through the cover region. The fielder stops the ball near the fence with a dive. Three taken.
Good run! Shortish and around off, Pujara dabs it on the off side and calls for a run. Rahane responds and they get it easily.
Shortish and around middle, bunted on the leg side by Pujara.

Gets a couple on the last ball to round off a good over for India. Full and on middle, Rahane clips this one to the deep square leg region. The fielder in the deep runs to his left and by the time he collects the ball, the batters run a brace. 7 runs off this over.
Good length and around off, Rahane defends.
Works the next one around off and middle towards fine leg for one.

FOUR! SHOT! Width offered and Pujara quickly goes on his back foot. It was a shortish length ball too so Pujara did well to get on top of the bounce and then cut it through backward point for a boundary.
Wide outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Full and around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.

Edgy! A length ball around off, Rahane looks to defend but this time the ball takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps, towards square leg. Pujara came forward looking for the single, but Rahane sends him back.
Landed around off on a good length, pushed towards point.

FOUR BYES! Cummins bangs this one short and bowls it around off and middle. Rahane sways away from the line. It goes well over the leaping Paine and goes to the fine leg fence. Four bonus runs for India.
Outside off, left alone by Rahane.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Fuller ball around off, Rahane drives it well but finds mid on.
Down the leg side. Pujara is not keen. Allows Paine to do the job. A productive over for India as they get 9 off it.
On off this time, Cheteshwar pushes this one to the cover region.
Back of a length and around off, Pujara blocks this one out to the leg side.

FOUR! Was in complete control of this shot! He saw an opportunity and he took it! Short and wide outside off, offering width to Pujara, he backs away and punches this one through cover-point and the ball wins the race to the ropes.

Mixed call from Rahane, but they get the single this time. A length delivery, around off, Rahane taps it towards the right of mid off. First, he calls no for the single. But right on the next instance, he changes his mind and says yes and takes off for the single. They get it quite easily, in the end.

EDGED AND FOUR AGAIN! Rahane gets lucky again. Another length ball around off, this one shapes away a touch as Rahane looks to drive. The outside edge is induced again. And it once again goes right between the third slip fielder and gully. This time it is closer to Wade but he has no chance to react as it goes rather quickly.
Another one that is just outside off on a length, Pujara allows Paine to collect it behind the wickets.
Good leave! A tight one from Pujara. This one is bowled very close to the off pole but Pujara trusts the bounce in the wicket and lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish and around off, Pujara blocks.
Length ball around off, poked towards gully.
Little too wide outside off to make Pujara play. He shoulders arms.
Shortish and around off, defended.

A dot and it is another testing over. Another ball that is just outside the off stump line. Rahane after playing that shot on the 2nd ball is a bit better prepared now it seems. He shoulders arms, 4th time in a row.
Another one in the channel outside off, left alone again.
Outside off again, Rahane lets it be.
Allows this one to go to the keeper by covering his wickets.

EDGED AND FOUR! There it is. Rahane is drawn forward again. A length ball outside off, Rahane comes on his front foot. He looks to drive but the ball takes the thick outside edge. It goes between the third slip fielder and gully. Green at gully dives to his left and tries to catch but the ball goes past him and into the fence. Nervy moment for Rahane.
Very full but wide outside off, the one that makes the batters go for the big booming drive. Rahane though is not lured.
Around off, Pujara defends it out.
Shortish again, this time Pujara stays back and works it towards square leg.
Cummins gets closer to the off pole. This is slightly short and around off, Pujara is solid again, in keeping this one out.
Outside off, left alone. Good carry to the keeper.
Banged short and around middle, Rahane pulls it towards square leg. Takes a run.
Fullish and around off, Rahane gets on his front foot to block.
A maiden to start from Starc. The last ball is around off on a length, Pujara is solid in defense.
Another one in the channel outside off, Pujara lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish but outside off, Pujara shoulders arms.
Back of a length and around off, Pujara keeps it out off his front foot.
Good length and around off, Pujara blocks it towards mid on.
A length ball angled in from outside off from Starc. Pujara tucks it towards square leg.
Who will partner Cummins with the cherry from the other end? Mitchell Starc, it is. 3-1-8-0 for him so far.
Fullish and around off, Rahane is solid in defense. Fine first over from Cummins.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fullish and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.

Lovely shot from the skipper! Full and just outside off, Rahane drives it through the cover region. Didn't hit it too hard, just a gentle push. The fielder from the cover position chases it down but not before Rahane and India get two.
Around off on a length again, right where he needs to be at the start of his spell. This time, Rahane is solid in defense.
Cummins is right on the money! A length ball just around off, Rahane looks to defend but it takes the inner half and goes towards square leg.

Right then. We are set to begin the first session of Day 3 now. The Australian players walk out and look to spread out to their respective positions out on the field. India's two overnight batters, Cheteshwar Pujara and Ajinkya Rahane follow them out and look to take their guard. Pat Cummins to begin proceedings for the hosts, with the ball in hand. He is ready. Here he comes...

Now, what will be on the mind of Australia? While the forecast for Day 3 is pretty good, the same cannot be said for the 4th and 5th days. As per the forecast, there will be plenty of rain in the last 2 days of this Test match. And if that's how things pan out, the Aussies would look to make sure they force a big collapse here on Day 3 to take control of the game. India, on the other hand, would look to try to get as close to the Aussie score as possible. Who will have it their way in the first session? We will soon find out as action isn't too far away. Stay with us.
