Hello and welcome to one and all. It is time for the moving day of the final Test match between Australia and India. The game hangs in balance at the moment after the action on Day 2. It was India who struck nice and early and eventually bundled the hosts in the extended first session. While Australia did get to an above-par first innings score, they missed out on the chance of putting an even bigger score. However, with the ball, they struck twice to make sure India didn't have an advantage after 2nd session on Day 2. Then came the rain and played a spoilsport and the entire final session was washed out.
... DAY 3, SESSION 1 ...

That's all from Day 2. The game hangs in the balance. The weather is expected to be clear on Day 3 but expect some spoilsport on the last couple of days. However, let's hope we get more action on Day 3 than what we got on Day 2. The action on Day 3 will begin 30 minutes prior to the scheduled start to cover the lost time. So, join us at 0930 local (2330 GMT THE PREVIOUS DAY) for all the action. Until then, it is goodbye from our end.

After that the Indians came out to bat. Cummins removed Gill early before Rohit and Pujara added 49. It was Rohit who scored most of the runs during that stand and was looking in supreme touch. However, he threw his wicket away as he tried to attack Lyon. After that, Pujara and Rahane made sure there wasn't another casualty before Tea. We went off for the break and rain arrived. It bucketed down at the Gabba and when it eventually stopped, it left the conditions wet. After a couple of inspections, the play was called off.

It was Shardul Thakur who struck for the visitors first as he got better of Paine. Sundar knocked over Green in the very next over and Shardul returned to send Cummins packing. Washington Sundar then snared his aussie counterpart, Nathan Lyon. Eventually, T Natarajan got his 3rd wicket of the game when he dismissed Hazlewood as the last wicket.

Earlier in the day, the Aussie overnight batters, Paine and Green, added a few runs before three wickets in quick succession fell to put India on top. Paine once again fell after getting to his half ton. However, Starc along with Lyon added a few valuable runs for his side and made sure Aussies crossed 350 comfortably.

Right! That's a bit disappointing end to the day's play. After Rohit got himself in, the Aussies stormed back in the game with his wicket. They were putting the duo of Pujara and Rahane under pressure before the Tea break. The Aussies would've loved a few more overs to have a go at the Indians but with the heavy downpour, it was impossible to have so.

Update 1650 Local (0650 GMT) - We hate to bring you some bad news, real bad news. Apparently the umpires had another look at the ground conditions and although rain did stop, they have deemed that the condtions are not fit for resumption of play. So, FURTHER PLAY HAS BEEN ABANDONED FOR DAY 2!

Till we get the latest news about the resumption of play, hear what Nathan has to say. Lyon starts off by saying that this ground dries pretty quickly. Is grateful for getting the wicket of Rohit Sharma, earlier, adding that the Indian batsman is a great player. On whether he has had a chance to speak to his parents regarding his milestone (100th Test), Gazza says that the players are in a bubble and hence he is not able to talk to them. But says that they are in the stands and are watching him play. Shane Warne prods him about Rishabh Pant and his rivalry with him, to which Gary says that Rishabh is always looking to tonk him out of the park. Jokingly remarks that his on-drive was the best shot that he has ever played and reckons that it was the shot of the series (albeit in a humorous manner).

Update 1625 Local (0625 GMT) - Well, we have visuals from the ground and we can say that THE SUN IS OUT! But we must also add that the ground still has some water and therefore, there is a second inspection scheduled at 1645 Local (0645 GMT). Let's hope we get to hear more positive news then...
Update 1550 Local (0550 GMT) - We have good news to present. It has stopped raining and the covers are coming off. We are hearing that there will be an inspection at 1615 Local time.

Update 1535 Local (0535 GMT) - It is that phase, where we as commentators turn more into giving you weather updates than being able to keep you updated on the match happenings. And that is because it still continues to pour down heavily at the Gabba. It will be a herculean task for the groundstaff to drain out the water, despite the presence of an excellent drainage system. But let's keep our fingers crossed and hope for the best...

Update 1505 Local (0505 GMT) - It is bucketing down at Brisbane now! Nothing unexpected, all on expected lines. Visuals of the ground show that it is absolutely pouring down. Some members of the crowd are enjoying themselves, match or shower. Let's hope though that the rain stops early and we get underway as quickly as possible.

Update 1520 Local (0520 GMT) - The latest scenes are not inspiring as it continues to rain in full swing. Looks like we are in for a long wait. The good thing though is that Gabba has an excellent drainage system. So, let's hope the rain goes away soon and we are back with the action, as early as possible.

Update 1500 Local (0500 GMT) - We are just getting live visuals from the ground that covers are coming on the square. Not that it is raining but it is very dark and Harsha Bhogle (on air) states that the groundsmen expect a hailstorm to arrive. Let's hope though that we can get underway soon. Stay tuned for the updates...

Right! A good, battling session of cricket ends. Rohit did well to keep the scoreboard ticking but Australia removed him just in time. Now, India's two top batters, Pujara and skipper Rahane are out in the middle. They will need to rebuild again when we return for the final session. Aussies, on the other hand, would love to see a few more wickets fall in the evening session. Remember, we might have rain interruptions in the final session as it has been forecasted. However, let's keep our fingers crossed. Be back soon for the last session on Day 2...

Australia bowled well in this session. They were patient throughout the period when Rohit was looking in decent touch. Cummins was the man for the Aussies to provide the first wicket, like he has done so many times. Lyon, playing his 100th Test, got the better of Rohit Sharma to make sure the honours are shared in this session. He got his 397th and is at the cusp of getting to 400 Test wickets. Hazlewood bowled tight lines and lengths and surprisingly, Mitch Starc got just 3 overs.

India started the session cautiously with Rohit and Gill doing well to play nearly the first 30 minutes of the session without much trouble. However, Gill got out without doing much but Rohit continued and he was looking in fluent touch. He hit a few glorious boundaries before falling into the trap of Lyon as he wanted to take him on. Rohit departed for 44, not too far from the Tea break. After his wicket, Pujara, along with Rahane made sure India went to the break without another hiccup.

A very good session of cricket, again! India were looking solid with Rohit looking in very good touch. However, the Aussies struck in time to make sure he wasn't running away with a big score. Both the teams wouldn't be too disappointed with the way things have gone in this session. Rohit, however, might be rueing inside the dressing room for the way he got dismissed.
Darted down the leg side, Pujara lets it be. Paine does well to move to his left to collect the ball. With that, it is Tea on Day 2.
Flatter and on middle, turned towards the leg side.
Loopy ball outside off, Pujara comes down the track and pushes it towards cover.
Slower through the air and outside off, Pujara comes down the track and pads it away.
Full and around off, Rahane comes down the track and taps it down to long on for one.
Looped up and around off, blocked.
Fuller and around off, Pujara blocks it towards mid on. A loud no from him.
Back of a length and on middle, pulled through square leg for one.
Length ball outside off, poked towards point by Ajinkya.
Around off on a good length, kept out.
Short again, Rahane cuts it off the toe end. No harm done though.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.
Another maiden. 4th one on the trot. Quicker one, around off, Pujara dabs it to the man at short leg.
On middle, tapped to short mid-wicket.

Flatter delivery on the stumps, Pujara comes down and looks to play at it but misses. Gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW but it is turned down. An alert Pujara gets back in his crease as short leg attempts to run him out at the keeper's end but misses to hit the stumps.
Comes down the track again and blocks this fuller ball.
Floated delivery around off, Cheteshwar dances down the track and defends it out. 'Bowl the arm ball, mate. Bowl the arm ball' says one of the Aussie players.
Gets across and taps the flatter ball to backward square leg.
Fullish this time, on middle, Rahane taps it to the off side.
Back to the fuller length and Rahane defends it out off the front foot.
Hazlewood goes for the short ball this time, Rahane sways away from the line of the ball.
Stands tall and punches this length delivery on the up. Cover-point dives and makes a stop.
Full length ball on the stumps, fended out to the off side.
Outside off, Ajinkya shoulders arms. Glenn McGrath (on air) reckons he should score quicker and put pressure on the hosts.

'Catch it' goes the shout but it hit the pads there. Flatter delivery, turning in, after pitching on middle. Cheteshwar goes back to play at it but misses. It comes off his pads and Wade, at short leg, goes back and takes it. Nothing much happens after that though. Tim says 'Bowling Gazza'.
On off and middle, stabbed to the leg side.
Comes down the track and pads it over silly point.

Another short one, outside off, Pujara pushes it with soft hands past silly point. The fielder there takes a couple of steps back, collects the ball and throws it back to Paine, but Pujara keeps his back foot inside the line there.
Stays on the back foot and fends this shorter ball out.
Flatter and around off, Cheteshwar goes back and clips it down to mid on.
It's getting really dark here at the Gabba!
Full length ball, the Indian skipper is solid in his defence.
Full length delivery, AR nudges it down to mid on. Oh.... some dark clouds are visible near the stadium. Let's hope that does not come down though.
On the leg pole, Ajinkya Rahane clips it to short mid-wicket. A 'no' follows to his partner again.
Full and outside the off stump line, Rahane, who initially looked to play at it, pulls back from doing so, as the ball passes him.
Attacks the woodwork with a fuller one, Ajinkya comes on the front foot and dabs it on the off side. A 'no' follows.
Josh Hazlewood is back on. 5-2-10-0 from him so far.
Length delivery on top of the stumps, blocked to the off side.
On off, clipped behind square on the on side.
The Indian skipper, Ajinkya Rahane, is in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Rohit Sharma departs. Commentator's curse works as Glenn McGrath (on air) was lavishing praise on Rohit previously. It is a good catch from Starcy. Lyon gets 397 wickets in Tests now. Full and around the off stump, Sharma skips down the track and looks to go big on the leg side. He though does not time it well and gets more of the elevation than distance. 'CATCH' is the shout. Mitchell, who was at long on, keeps his eyes on the ball, runs forward, tumbles and takes a very good catch. A well set Rohit Sharma has to walk back now. He needed to be there for more, but has failed to do so, Rohit.
Floated delivery around the off pole line, pushed to the right of the bowler, who gets there and stops it.
FOUR! Wonderful shot. Sharma has looked wonderful today. Short and wide outside the off pole, cannot give him room. And he shows why. Rohit punches it through point for a boundary.
Full length ball outside off, Rohit comes forward and blocks it.
Full ball on the pads, Pujara flicks it through square leg for a single.
A solid front foot block to see off the over as Green bowls the last ball full and around off.
In the channel outside off, left alone.

FOUR! BOOM! Rohit moves to 40. That is solid timing from Rohit. Classy batting from Hitman here. A fuller ball from Green. It is around off, Rohit once again just has a gentle push. It races through mid off. Labuschagne gives it a chase. Dives but this time he is not getting there. Top stroke. Shot of the day maybe.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, Rohit drives it fluently but finds the cover fielder.
Some rest for Pat as Cameron Green replaces him. Cameron has bowled just the 2 overs for 7 runs so far. Interesting move.
Comes down the track again, flicks the ball towards mid-wicket.
Loopy ball outside off, Pujara pads it away.
Shortish and around off and middle, turning in. Rohit clips it towards short fine leg. Pujara calls for a quick run. Rohit responds.
Rohit jumps out of his crease, Lyon reads that plan early and darts it wide. Rohit does well to block.
Looped up and outside off, Rohit lets it be.
Tossed up and around off, pushed to mid off by Rohit.
Length ball just outside off, poked towards point for nothing. 9 off the over, a productive one for India.
Banged short and Rohit instinctively goes for the pull. Mistimes it off the inner half of the bat towards deep square leg for one. 50 up for the visitors.
FOUR! SHOT! Cummins overpitches it and bowls it around off and middle, Rohit gently pushes it down the ground and it races away through mid on.
Back of a length and around off, Rohit gets on his toes to block.
Length ball around off, blocked.
EDGY FOUR! Length ball just outside off, Rohit comes on the front foot and looks to defend.  Does that with soft hands and it goes through the gap between gully and third slip.
Flatter and outside off, Rohit punches it wide of the backward point fielder for one. 3 from Lyon's first over.
On off, kept out.
Shortish and around off, punched towards cover-point for one.
Tossed up and outside off again, Pujara tucks it on the leg side this time.

Looped up and around off, Pujara comes on the front foot and looks to defend. He misses and the ball hits his pads and falls to silly point there. They go up in appeal, presumably for the catch, but it is not given. Posing some early questions, Nathan Lyon.
Tossed up and outside off, Rohit comes on the front foot and pushes it towards point to take a run.

When you hear 'Nice Gary' and 'Bowling Gazza', that can mean only one person, THE GOAT! Yes, Nathan Lyon is in to bowl now. A momentous occassion for him. It is his 100th Test game and his family is in the stands as well. 4 wickets shy of 400 in Tests, can Lyon bag them in this very innings? Let's find out...
Length ball around off, kept out.
Good length and outside off, comes back in but Rohit trusts the bounce and lets it go to Paine.
Short and around off, Rohit goes for the pull. Doesn't time it that well but it goes to mid-wicket. Off the inner half for one.
Shortish and around off, Rohit keeps it out.
Length ball outside off, Rohit shoulders arms.
Full and outside off, Rohit drives it well but finds the mid off fielder who moves to his left to field.
Wide outside off, Pujara watches it go to the keeper.
Green goes full and it is on the pad. Pujara looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pad.
Outside off, left alone.
On the pads of Rohit this time, he clips it through square leg for one.

FOUR! Short and wide and Rohit pounces on the scoring opportunity. Too short and too wide, Rohit slashes it through backward point for a boundary. There was shouts of catch but that went like a tracer bullet and nobody had a chance.
Landed around off on a length, pushed to mid on.

Edged but short! Cummins induces the edge again, of Pujara. A fulll ball outside off. It is juicy enough for Pujara to go for the drive. He does that but gets an outside edge that falls short of Smith at second slip.
Fuller and around off, blocked towards mid on.
Some distraction here. Somebody in the stands seems to be catching Pujara's attention, behind the sight screen. That is sorted and we are back to the action...
Length ball around off, defended off the front foot.
Banged short but down the leg side. Rohit look to pull but makes no connection.

Rohit's turn to hit it down the ground! A fuller ball around off, Rohit meets it with straight bat and drives it through mid off. The ball is racing towards the fence but Labuschagne gives it a chase and makes a diving stop near the fence. Saves a run as the batters take three.

Nicely pushed down the ground. Just a gentle push that is all, reckons Allan Border (on air). Full length ball just outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara nudges it wide of mid off. The fielder there turns back, runs and keeps it out before it reaches the boundary. Three taken in the meanwhile though.

DRINKS! A tough hour for India comes to an end. Australians have landed an early blow by netting the in-form Shubman Gill, courtesy a peach from Patrick Cummins. And Pujara, survived by just, on the very next ball, with the outside edge falling just short of Smith, at second slip. With not a great deal of batting depth or experience to follow, much rests on these two's shoulders to carry forward the Indian innings. Let's see if they can brave the storm (the bowling one, we meant) after the mini-break...
Landed around off on a length, poked towards point.
Shortish and around off, blocked out by Rohit.
Full and just outside off, Rohit drives it wide of the mid off fielder for a brace.
Angled in from middle and leg, Rohit looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Fuller and outside off, left alone.
Cameron Green to bowl now. Here he comes to Rohit...
Fullish and around off, Rohit defends it out.
Full and around the off stump, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend but ends up getting an inside edge there. It though goes past the stumps safely.

Full length ball on the off pole, defended to short mid-wicket off the inner half. Harsha (on air) stresses on the importance to bat well. He reckons there is not much batting depth in the Indian line-up and hence it is imperative for the set batsmen to bat well.
Full length ball outside off, Pujara plays it with soft hands. The man at gully dives but fails to keep it out. Two runs taken as Nathan runs towards the ball and retrieves it.
Short, down the leg side, Cheteshwar ducks under that one.
Full length delivery on off and middle, defended back on the track.

Shortish and on off and middle, dabbed down to mid on. Warne (on air) reckons India need to bat well now. He feels it will get tougher to bat, going forward, to which Harsha Bhogle pulls his legs and asks him to say something nice to the Indian fans.
Length ball around off, blocked off the front foot.
Shortish and just outside off, pushed towards point.
In the channel outside the off stump area again, this time for Rohit. He too lets it be.
Pujara is up and running. Shortish and just around off, Pujara pokes it towards backward point for a single.
In the channel outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Good length and around off, Cheteshwar keeps it out off his front foot.
Around off on a length, Rohit is solid in defense.
Good length this time, it is pushed towards point.
Fullish and around off, kept out.
FOUR! Full and outside off, Rohit leans into the shot and looks to drive. It goes through point off the outer half of the bat.
Fullish and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball around off, it is driven nicely but straight to mid off.
Full and around off, Pujara keeps it out.

Huge appeal but turned down by the umpire. No review from Australia. They gave it a thought though. A length ball around off and middle, it comes back in as Rohit looks to work it on the leg side. He misses and gets hit high on the pad. A loud appeal follows but the umpire is not interested. They cross ends as the ball goes to the leg side. Run given which means the umpire thought that there was some bat there. Inside edge maybe.
Good running! Back of a length ball on middle, Rohit pulls it down to deep square leg for two.
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Angled in from well outside off, Rohit shoulders arms but it jags back in sharply. Clips the top of his pads but no danger for the Indian batter there.
Length ball around off, blocked.
Good length and on middle, Rohit clips it through square leg for a brace. Called no ball as Josh has overstepped.
Shortish and around middle, Pujara gets on his toes and blocks. End of a wicket-maiden from Cummins.
Fullish and just outside off again, Pujara pushes it towards gully.
Landed on a length and around middle, clipped towards square leg.

Edged again but this one falls short. Absolutely terrific stuff from Cummins here. A fuller ball just outside off, Pujara pokes at the first ball, once again with hard hands. This time the outside edge goes to the left of Smith and it keeps low. Smith lunges forward and tries to catch but it bounces before him.
Cheteshwar Pujara walks out to bat at No. 3. Exactly the situation that requires his sort of patient, steady state of play.

OUT! TAKEN! Australia draw first blood. It is that man again. Pat Cummins, the number one Test bowler in the world. Terrific from Cummins. Good length and just outside off, it pitches and then shapes away. Gill stays rooted in his crease and looks to poke at it. He does that with hard hands and ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes to the right side of Steven Smith at second slip. Smudge there is safe as houses as he gobbles the chance easily.
Fullish and just outside off, Gill lets it be. Some movement for Pat but it is after the ball goes past the batsman.
Pat Cummins has the ball now.
Maiden over as Rohit gets beaten here! Hazlewood runs in from wide of the crease and angles a fuller length ball near off, Sharma looks to defend from within the crease but misses to do so.
Length and around off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Short ball way down the leg side. Rohit goes for the pull but makes no connection.
Tight from Hazlewood. It is around off on a good length, Rohit pushes it towards mid on.
Good length and around off and middle, blocked on the off side.
Fullish and around off, Rohit lunges forward and blocks solidly.
Solid again. Rocks onto the back foot, presents the full face of the bat and defends this shortish length ball to the off side.
Full and on off and middle, defended to the off side.

Well left. Nick Knight (on air) emphasises on the importance of leaving and felt that it was a good leave. Just outside off on a length, Gill judges it well and leaves it. Nick says he needs to keep doing it throughout the innings.
Outside off, Gill shoulders arms.

FOUR! Beautiful. He is very strong on the back foot. Plays it with an angled bat. Shortish length delivery, outside the off stump area, Shubman transfers his weight on the back foot, gets on top of the bounce and punches it through the covers.

False shot but will still get two runs. Full length ball, Gill looks to flick that but ends up getting it off the inner half there. It goes through mid-wicket and the Indians collect a brace. 'Bowling Mitch' says an Aussie player.
4 overs done and India are 5/0. Very full length delivery on off and middle, dug out back to the bowler.
Fullish length ball around the off pole area, Rohit Gurunath Sharma stands tall and blocks it back on the pitch.
Full length delivery, nicely clipped away, to the left of fine leg. Should get two and they do get it.
Full and on the off stump channel, fended out to the off side.
Fullish length ball on the off pole channel, solidly defended.
SG gets off the mark now. On the pads, he clips it down to fine leg and crosses over for a single.
Sensibly left alone this time as it was shortish and outside the off stump line.

BEATEN! Ohh... that has hit the crack. Fullish length delivery around the off stump channel, hits the crack and seams away from the outside edge of the Mumbaikar, as he looked to defend that. Mitch has a smile after beating Sharma there.
Back of a length delivery outside the off stump area, Sharma lets that one be.
Short and outside off, this time he shoulders arms.
Shortish length delivery, around the off stump, Rohit moves a little in his crease and drives it on the up to cover-point.
Hops a little and stabs the short length delivery to the man at cover-point.
Good first over from Hazlewood. This one is banged in shortish and on top of the stumps, SG stands tall and fends it out.
BEATEN! 'Ohh'.... says Josh there. Lands it on a length and just outside the off pole line, Shubman Gill stands tall and looks to block but the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Outside off, left alone.
Stands tall and dabs the short pitched delivery to the leg side.
Short of a length and outside off, defended out to cover-point.
Solid defense. Full and on the off pole, blocked firmly. Nick Knight (on air) is eager to see how Gill will go about. Reckons he is a super talent.
Will it be Pat Cummins to partner Starc from the other end? No, it is Josh Hazlewood.
And the first over is done. Well outside off on a length, the Mumbai lad lets it be. 2 runs then from the first over.
'Confident and Elegant' says Murali Kartik (on air). The Hitman is off the mark. Comes forward and pushes the full length ball through the covers. Picks up a couple as it is fielded.
Solid push. Full length delivery, just outside off, RS comes on the front foot and defends it to the off side.

Wider than the last one, outside off, fuller in length, Rohit Sharma plants his front foot across, only to let it go in the end. But look at that carry! Tim Paine takes all three deliveries so far, with fingers pointing towards the sky.
Better than the last one. On a length and outside the off pole area, Sharma leaves it.
Pretty wayward. Short and well outside off, Rohit is not going to have a go at that at all.

So, we have got a match in our hands. Rain after that brief entry has stayed away from this game. Plenty of time left on Day 4, provided rain stays away. Final innings of this long Test series coming your way shortly.

With the lead of 276, the Aussies wanted to add a few more to that score. However, Starc couldn't add any run to his score as Siraj sent him packing in the 2nd over of the session. Lyon and Cummins played a few shots before they were removed by Shardul and Siraj as Australia were bowled out for 294 and with the lead of 327. Siraj got a fifer with Shardul helping him by taking the catch. Shardul himself got a 4-fer.

Right! India have bowled Australia out. Siraj is leading the Indian unit as they go off and get ready for their batting. Siraj shows the ball to the crowd as he walks off. A fine performance from the man.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mohammed Siraj gets his maiden 5-wicket haul. What a moment and series to get. Bowls a short one around off, Hazlewood tries to uppercut it but ends up slicing it towards third man where Shardul Thakur who had 4 wickets to his name takes the catch to help his partner get to a 5-wicket haul. AUSTRALIA BOWLED OUT FOR 294 RUNS!
FOUR! Class shot! Full and on off, Hazlewood drives it through covers and gets the boundary.
A mix up but all safe in the end. Length ball around off, pushed to covers as Cummins takes the single. He looks to take the second but is sent back as the throw comes to the bowler's end.
Length and on middle, Cummins pushes it with soft hands towards slips. The ball goes on the bounce to Rohit Sharma.
Short of good length around off, Cummins pulls it to mid-wicket for no run.
Full and on off, driven straight down the ground towards mid off this time by Hazlewood.
BEATEN! Length and wide outside off, Hazlewood backs away as he goes for the wild swing but misses it as the ball goes past his outside edge.
Full and on off, Cummins lofts it uppishly towards long off where the fielder takes it on the bounce. A single taken.
WDE! A bumper on off, too high to make Cummins play at it. The square leg umpires gives it a wide.
Length and on off, Cummins hops inside his crease and defends it out to the off side.
Short of length and around off, Josh plays it uppshly towards third man for a single.
Beaten! Length and on off, Hazlewood tries to guide it to the third man region but fails in the end. The ball goes past the outside edge.
Good length and on middle, it is played back to the bowler. Josh was backing up there but Siraj didn't throw the ball. If he had a shy and if he had hit, he would've got Josh there.
Length and down leg, Cummins looks to play the short arm jab but ends up missing it altogether.
Full and straight on off, driven towards mid off where a fumble allows the batsman to take a couple of runs.
Length and on off, pushed to the leg side by Cummins.
SIX! That's slogged! Slower ball well outside off, Cummins backs away and slogs it way high and over the fence at long on for a biggie.
Full and on off, driven straight down to the bowler.
Length and on off, kept out off the back foot.
FOUR! Gloriously driven! Full and outside off, Hazlewood opens his arms and drives it through covers for a boundary. These are useful runs for Australia.
Shortish and around middle, blocked.
Length and on off, Josh plays it off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Hazlewood drives it towards gully.
Josh Hazlewood is the last man in.
Josh Hazlewod is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! In the air and taken! That's wicket number 4 for Shardul Thakur. Short and around off, Lyon goes to swat it to the off side. But it hits the higher part of the bat and goes towards covers where Mayank Agarwal takes it with ease. Australia are 9 down!
BEATEN! Short of a good length around off, Cummins swings hard but can only connect with thin air.
Full and on off, Cummins swings hard but cannot beat the man at mid on.
Low full toss, Lyon looks to drive but the ball takes the inner half and goes to square leg for a single.
SIX! Goes all the way! Superb from Lyon. Banged short and on middle, Lyon swivels and pulls it over fine leg for a biggie.
A single now and the lead is 300 now. Length ball around off, it is pulled down to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full and outside off, Cummins drives but finds mid off.
Fuller and around off, driven well but straight to mid off.
Play and a miss! Length ball outside off, Lyon looks to punch it on the up but he misses.
Short and outside off, Cummins pulls and hits it through mid-wicket. Before long on can come around, they take three.
NO BALL! Short and wide outside off, Cummins lets it be. Called no ball.
Looks to pull this time but makes no connection.
Another bouncer! Cummins decides not to take it on. He sits under it.
Banged short, Lyon pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
Good length and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
WIDE! Another sharp bumper! Cummins sways away. The square leg umpire calls it wide.
Superb bouncer! Cummins does well to move out of the way.
Full and around off, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Short and around off, pulled down to square leg for one. A slight fumble but they don't go for the run.

EDGY FOUR! Useful runs! Siraj lands this around off, maybe on one of those cracks. It came back in sharply. Smith looks to keep it out but it hits his elbow and races down to the fine leg fence, past his stumps. Runs given though.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Banged short, Cummins manages to help it down to fine leg for a single.
Short ball around off, Pat pulls but finds mid on.
Shortish and just outside off, tapped to the left of deep cover for a brace.
Length and around off, played back to the bowler.
Fuller and around middle, clipped to long on for one.
Length ball around off, a solid front foot defense.
Edged but short! Length and around off, Cummins looks to defend but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes to second slip but falls well short. End of a successful over from Siraj.
Short and wide outside off, Cummins cuts it hard but Rahane intercepts nicely at gully.
Shot! What a shot from Lyon to get off the mark. A fuller ball around off, Lyon hits it through mid on and gets three. 250 up for the Aussies. The lead now goes to 283.
Nathan Lyon is out to bat. Can he and Cummins get Australia to a score in excess of 300 runs on the lead?

OUT! CAUGHT! Siraj removes Starc and gets his 4th here. A fuller ball outside off, Starc looks to hammer it over mid off but he ends up hitting it off the outer half. It goes to the left of Saini at mid off who moves that side and gobbles the catch easily. India just 2 away from bundling the Aussies.
Play and a miss! Fullish and outside off, going away. Starc throws the willow but makes no connection.
Shortish and around off, blocked.
Who will bowl from the other end? Mohammed Siraj to bowl now. 15-5-42-3 so far from him.
Length and outside off, left alone by Cummins.
Concussion check time, just because of the mendatory rule. Funnily, the physio has a word or two and goes off. Nothing serious there.
Slower short ball on leg, Cummins sits under it. The ball though brushes back of his helmet a bit before going to the keeper.

FOUR! Throws the kitchen sink at it! Full and wide outside off, Cummins thows the bat at it to get an edge. The ball flies over the slips and into the fence at third man for a boundary. That is what is expected from the Australian tail.
Length and down leg, Cummins looks to tickle it fine but misses it.
Starts with a bumper after resumption as Cummins sits under it.

We are back after the rain and Tea break. The Aussies would look to score some brisk runs with Mitchell Starc and Pat Cummins out there before thinking of declaring their innings. The Indian team is also ready on the field. Shardul Thakur to complete his uncomplete over. Here we go...
... Day 4, Session 3 ...

UPDATE 1520 local ( 0520 GMT) -  Well, well, the covers are being peeled off. Good signs. Looks like we will get the action soon. Live pictures show that the umpires walking out without umbrellas to discuss the start time with the groundsmen. There was rain predicted due to the storm but luckily it hasn't rain that much as we wait for the start. We have a start time. Play to resume at 1530 local (0530 GMT). Stay tuned.

UPDATE 1455 local (0455 GMT) - We should have had a start by now for the final session but the rain continues to pour down. The covers are firmly placed at the moment as it has gone a bit gloomy. Stay tuned for further updates.

Right! We are done with the 2nd session. The predicted rain has arrived. The covers are on now. Let's hope it is just a passing shower and we are back for the final installment of Day 4 soon. Stick with us for further updates.

The Indians kept taking wickets regularly in this session. The Aussies went after the bowlers and that meant that plenty of runs were scored. Siraj and Shardul bowled nicely in this session and picked up wickets. Saini and Natarajan struggled in their spells and gave away easy runs. Sundar kept things tight for the visitors.

The session started with Smith hitting a few boundaries to reach his half ton. He was put down by Siraj off Sundar but the pacer returned to send him packing soon. Green then along with Paine added a few more runs to take the lead over 250 before falling to Shardul Thakur. Paine got into the thick of things and hit a few boundaries before getting caught behind. Rain arrived just before the Tea break to end the session.

Another battling session of cricket and one would assume this one has been shared as well The Aussies always wanted to attack and they did that but lost a few wickets in the process. The one thing that is in their favor is the way the ball is misbehaving after hitting a few cracks. That will excite the Aussie quicks and Lyon for sure. In this session  25.1 overs were bowled and 94 runs were scored as Australia extended the lead to 276 runs.
Update 1432 local (0432 GMT) - The drizzle has got heavier! And off we go. With Tea just a few minutes away, the umpires rightly call it end of the session. It is TEA on Day 4.
It has started to drizzle. It has come out of nowehre. Not too heavy and hence they want to continue.
Length and around middle, clipped behind square on the leg side for a single.
Lovely bowling! Length and around off, Cummins looks to have a feel of the ball as he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and around off, blocked towards covers by Cummins from within the crease.
Full on off, driven straight to mid off from the front foot by Cummins.
Length and outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.
On middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
EDGED BUT WELL SHORT! Length and around off, Cummins looks to defend it out off the back goot but the ball takes the outside edge and drops short of the first slip fielder.
Mitchell Starc is the new man in. Change in bowling as well. Here's T Natarajan.

OUT! CAUGHT! A sharp catch from Rishabh Pant there. Thakur picks up his third. A short around off, Paine swivels to pull but ends up getting a top edge which goes towards Pant who takes the catch over his head. He timed the jump to perfection there. Takes it and jumps in jubilation. Shardul is pumped as well. The lead is now 275 runs!
Fuller and on off, Paine gets low to push this one towards mid on this time.
Good length and around off, Paine blocks it out.
Short and outside off, slapped through covers for a couple.
Length and outside off, Paine lets it be this time.
Length and on off, kept out from the crease by Paine.
Paine looks to make room. Sundar follows him. Paine manages to force it towards deep point for a single.
Turning in from just outside off, Paine looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad.
Tossed up on leg, spinning down leg, left alone.
FOUR! Innovative from Paine! Sundar tosses it up and and bowls it on middle, Paine brings out the reverse sweep. Nails it through point and finds consecutive boundaries.
FOUR! Flicked away! Tossed up on leg, Paine just tickles it fine towards fine leg as the ball goes onto meet the fence there.
Tossed up on off, Paine misses his tuck as the ball hits his pads. There is an appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Length and down leg, wayward from Thakur as Cummins goes for the pull only to miss it. Pant does well to get it off one-hand by running to his left.
Full and on midlde, clipped towards mid-wicket off the back foot by Cummins.
Fuller and outside off, Cummins does not disturb the path of the ball there as he lets it go through to the keeper.
Length and outside off, Cummins shoulders arms to it.
Short of good length around off, Paine punched it off the back foot through covers for a single.
SHOT! Full and around off, Paine plays a handsome cover drive but fails to get it past the fielder there.
Beaten! Darted just around off, Cummins looks to defend it off his back foot but fails to connect.
Flighted on off, Cummins manages to keep it away to the off side off the back foot.
Floated down leg, Cummins does not fiddle with it.
Rohit has a chat with the bowler.
Fuller and on off, whipped past the short mid-wicket fielder for a couple of runs. Cummins off the mark.
Flaoted on off, pushed to covers by Cummins who looks to get off the mark but is sent back by Paine.
Tossed up on off, pushed back down the ground towards long on for a single.
Change in bowling. Washington Sundar is back on.
In the channel outside off, Cummins leaves it alone. End of a successful over for Shardul.
Pat Cummins is the new man in. Time for some slogging as Australia eye the 300-run mark with the lead.

OUT! TAKEN AT SECOND SLIP! Lovely bowling from Shardul. Lands the length ball just around off, Green pokes at it away from his body as the ball bounces extra. It takes the outside edge and goes to the right of Rohit. The Indian opener takes the chance easily. 5th catch for him in this game. End of a battling knock for Green.
Length and around off, blocked towards mid on this time.
Back of a length and around off, kept out.

Quick single! Direct hit would've made things a bit interesting. A fuller ball around off, Paine pushes it towards mid off and goes for a risky run. The fielder there has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses.
A fuller ball around off and middle to begin, Paine flicks it uppishly. It is to the right of Gill but it just falls short.
Shardul Thakur is back on. 11-2-36-1 from him so far.
A single and it is 9 off it now. Short and just outside off, punched down to deep point for a single. Another expensive over from Saini. He is leaking runs here.
FOUR! Down the ground again. This time it is Paine. Just forces it through mid on and this time Sundar is not chasing it. 8 off the over already.
Three more! Runs coming fast for the Aussies again. A fullish ball around off, Green drives it through mid on. Sundar gives it a chase and dives to make a stop. Saves a run for the side.
Shortish and around off, played back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on middle, Paine clips it through square leg for a run.
Full and around off, stroked to mid off for nothing.
Banged short and on middle and leg, Green sits under it.
Short and around middle, Paine tucks it wide of the man at mid on for a single. The lead reaches 250 runs!
Another one outside off, Paine makes another leave.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Short and wide outside off, Paine punches it well but straight to the point fielder.
Back of a length and around off, pushed towards point off the toes.

Shot! Full and on middle, Paine flicks it past mid on. The fielder dives to his right to stop but misses. Has to get up and return to the keeper by chasing it near the fence. That allows the batters to take three. 10 from the over, a good one for the Aussies. The lead is now 249.
Good length and around middle, Paine looks to work it on the leg side but he misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Length and around off, Paine pushes it towards mid on.
Short and around off, tapped on the off side for a quick run.
FOUR! Poor from Saini. He offers width and bowls it short too. Green slams it through backward point for a boundary.
Length ball around off, it is flicked through mid-wicket for a brace.
Navdeep Saini is back on.  3-1-13-0 from him so far.
Full and wide outside off, Green drives it hard towards the right side of the cover fielder who dives and makes a half stop. A single.
Good shot but for no run. Full and outside off, Green drives it hard but finds mid off.
On the pads this time. Paine tucks it towards fine leg for a run.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on for nothing.
Shortish and around off, it is tapped in front of the point fielder for one.
Full and around off, Paine pushes it to the left of the cover fielder for a single.

DRINKS! Once again the session began with Australia taking the bowling apart and once again India managed to crawl back into the game. Just when the Smith-Green stand was starting to get stronger Siraj strikes to send Smith back into the hut. That ball to Smith rose viciously off the surface. That should concern India too as they are to bat last. The lead has gone past the 200-run mark and closing in onto 250. Can India finish it off quickly to get the game in their grasp? As the more the lead the difficult it will be for India. Stay tuned for another hour of intriguing session.
FOUR! Swept and swept well. Tossed up and outside off, Green drags the ball from there and sends it past the square leg fielder and into the fence.
Full and around off, Green comes back and blocks back to the bowler.
Flat and around off, poked towards point.
Paine is underway! Flat and around middle and leg, Paine clips it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Full and on middle, stroked to long on for one.
Tossed up and around off, kept out.
Fuller and around off, Paine pushes it back to Siraj. A wicket maiden from him.
Length ball around off, kept out.
Another cobra from Siraj. It hits the crack and bounces extra. Paine is not sure how to play at it. Manages to fend it off towards the off side.
Fullish and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tim Paine is the new man in. He managed to get a 50 in the first innings, can replicate that form again?

OUT! TAKEN! The glove is in the cotact of the bat and Smith has to go. He wasn't sure about it and hence went for the review. A lovely ball from Siraj. A length ball around off, this one shoots off after hitting the deck. Smith fends at it awkardly. The ball hits his gloves and goes to the left of Rahane at gully. The Indian skipper is not going to drop it. The Indians celebrate. Smith has a word with his partner at the other end. He is suggesting that maybe his hand was off the glove when the ball kissed it. And hence he goes for the review. Replays roll in and they show otherwise. So, the onfield call will stay. Siraj's twin drops doesn't cost India much. A fine knock from Smith comes to an end.

Smith has been given out! He reviews it as he is'nt sure whether his hand was holding the handle or no when the ball brushed the glove. Let's see what the replays have to say. Ohh! That is out as Smith is holding the bat when the ball brushes his glove on its way to the fielder at gully. The on field call stays.
Fullish and around off, kept out.
FOUR! Tossed up and outside off, Green sweeps it and finds the fence at deep square leg.
Flatter and just outside off, Green manages to push it towards third man for a brace.
Fuller and around middle, flicked to silly mid on.
On middle, clipped towards the leg side for a single.
EDGED AND FOUR! Tossed up around off, Smith looks to go for the drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball rolls towards the third man region as it crosses the fence there.
Flatter and around off, blocked.
Just outside off on a good length, blocked.
Length and around off, pushed to mid on.

DROPPED! Siraj drops one off his own bowling this time. Green gets a life. Full and straight on off, Green strokes it straight down the ground. It is a bit uppish as Siraj goes for the catch but ends up spilling it. That should have been taken. How costly would the drop of Green prove for India?
Full and on off, driven straight to the point fielder.
BEATEN! Length and outside off, Green looks to defend it out but is beaten on the outside edge.
Length and on middle, clipped towards square leg for a dot.
Mohammed Siraj is back on. 11-3-37-2 from him so far.
Flat and around off, Smith works it towards square leg again.
Flatter and around middle, tucked on the leg side for nothing.
On off, pushed to mid off for a quick single.
FIFTY FOR SMITH! A fine knock that has come at a brisk pace. Shortish and around middle, tucks around the corner for a single. His 31st half ton in the format.
Full and around off, played back to the bowler.
Tossed up and around off, played to mid on.
Angled in from around off and middle, Green looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes to fine leg. They take two leg byes.
Length ball around off, pushed to mid on.
Banged short and down the leg side. Green looks to bang it on the leg side but makes no connection.
Shortish and just outside off, kept out.
Fullish and around off, blocked to mid on.
Shot! Shortish and just outside off, Smith punches it to the left of the cover fielder. The fielder dives to his left but fails to stop. Three more for Smith. He moves to 49.
Flatter and around off, Green goes back to block.
Flat and around off, Green comes down the track and pushes it towards the bowler.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and around off, kept out.
Fired on middle, Smith looks to paddle it down the leg side but misses. The keeper fails to collect and they take a bye.

DROPPED AND FOUR! How costly will that be? A tossed up ball around off, Smith jumps out of his crease and looks to go downtown. He mistimes it towards long on where Siraj misjudges the catch. Gets both hands but it pops out and goes to the fence. Sundar cannot believe it.
Manages to work the last ball towards mid-wicket. A testing over.
Green gets another blow on the body. This one pitches and comes back in again. It bounces extra to beat the bat. Green gets hit near the box.
Appeal for LBW but that looked to be going down the leg side. Angled in from around off, Green looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. They appeal but not out says the umpire.
Length and around off, Green looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
That kept really low. How did that ball miss the stumps. A length ball outside off, it hits the crack and keeps low. Green looks to defend but misses.
Length and around off, defended.

FOUR! BOOM! Smith into the 40s now! Tossed up and around off, Smith makes room and dances down the ground. Gets to the pitch of the ball and nails the drive through mid off. Super shot. 50-run stand is also up between these two.
On the pads, clipped to the left of square leg fielder for one more.
Full and on middle, this time Green flicks it wide of the man at long on. Two taken and the lead goes over 200.
Full and on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Floated on middle and leg, it turns in as Green lets it be. Pant does well to move to his left to collect.
Full and on the pads, Green comes down the track and looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. A mild appeal.
Washington Sundar is back on. 11-1-38-1 from him so far.
Full and just outside off, driven to mid off for nothing.
Around off on a length, kept out.
Fullish and outside off, Green drives it through backward point and gets three. The lead reads 199 now.
Full and around off, Smith drops it in front of the cover fielder for a quick run.
Good length and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Fuller and outside off, pushed wide of the man at mid off for one.
Length and on midlde, clipped towards mid-wicket by Green for a single as he keeps the strike for the next over.
Another fuller length ball on off, pushed down the ground off the back foot. Shardul too slips in his followthrough there.
Length and around off, defended off the back foot by Green.
Fuller and on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Hammered! Short and outside off, Smith pulls it and gets it towards mid-wicket as the ball meets the fence.
Full and on middle, clipped to the leg side for a single.
In the air...Just short! Full and on leg, Smith clips it uppishly towards square leg where it falls just short of Rohit Sharma. Lucky there is Smith.
Full and on off, Smith blocks it right from within the crease.
Another full ball on the pads, Smith flicks it straight to square leg this time.
Another one angled into off and middle, Smith turns it off the front foot towards mid-wicket once again.
Full and on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket by Smith there.
Fuller on leg, Smith plays it to mid on. Natarajan oversteps! NO BALL CALLED!
Short of good length on off, Smith punched it straight to the cover fielder.
BEATEN! Length and outside off, Green looks to punch it from within the crease but ends up missing it altogether as the ball goes past his outside edge.
Length and outside off, Green punched it crisply towards covers to find the fielder there.
Length and on off, punched off the back foot towards the bowler by Green.
Short and wide outside off, slapped through point for a single as there is protection in the deep there.
Length and on off, pushed to mid off from within the crease.
Length and on off, turned towards mid on this time by Smith.
A single to end the over! Full and on leg, clipped towards fine leg by Smith.
Fuller and on middle, Smith strokes it straight towards mid-wicket.
Another one going down leg, easy leave for Smith there.
Length and down the leg, left alone.
Length and on off, pushed to mid on.
Full and on the pads, Smith flicks it through to fine leg. A couple taken in the end. 150 comes up for Australia.
Who will bowl from the other end for India? T Natarajan it is.
Maiden from Thakur to begin the new session. The last ball is wide outside off, so Green leaves it alone again.
Just outside off on a good length. Another leave from Green.
Fuller and around middle, stroked straight to mid on.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Gets behind the line of the ball this time to defend.
Good leave! Close leave. Good start from Shardul. This one pitches just outside off, hits a crack and comes back in. Green covers his stumps and lets it be.

We are back for the post Lunch session. Steven Smith and Cameron Green have a task in hand to take Australia to total from where losing seems far fetched as they make their way out. They are followed by the Indian players who would look to finish of the innings before Tea to have a chance of a win. Shardul Thakur to start the session with the ball.
... DAY 4, SESSION 2 ...

Right! Australia's lead reds 182. Smith still out in the middle and looking really good. The weather doesn't look too bad. Another similar session for the Aussies and they will be able to see a total excess of 300. And If that happens, they will give themselves a good chance of having a crack at the Indians. The visitors, on the other hand, would look to get rid of Smith as quickly as possible in the second session. How will things pan out? We will find out in the afternoon session. The second session coming your way in a short while.

Indians gave away a few boundaries too many in the first hour of play as Warner and Harris punished them. It looked like they will boss the session. However, Shardul amid a fantastic spell got the wicket of Harris and provided the much-needed breakthrough for the Indians. Sundar removed dangerous Warner in the very next over. Labuschagne and Smith came with a positive mindset and attacked the bowlers. However, before that stand got bigger, Siraj removed Labuschagne with a brilliant delivery. He struck in the same over to get rid of Wade. They kept things tight after that.

The day started with Warner and Harris scoring briskly with the help of a few streaky boundaries early on. They put a lot of pressure on the Indians in the first hour. The duo took the lead to over 100. However, both departed in consecutive overs as India tried to make a comeback. However, Labuschagne and Smith counter-attacked as they added 32 in just 27 balls. However, Labuschagne got out and Wade followed him back to the pavilion without opening his account as India forced them on the back foot. After that Smith, along with Green negotiated the remaining over to remain unscathed till the Lunch break.

What a session of play! 128 runs for Australia in this session and it has come at a brisk pace too. However, like it has been the case throughout the series, India after being pushed on the back foot, have stormed back in the game with 4 wickets. It has made sure that the Aussies have not run away with the game.
Fuller and on off, Smith guides it to point where the substitute Prithvi Shaw fields it. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY4!
Full and on off, pushed to mid on off the  back foot once again by Smith.
Full and on off, Smith defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Smith's merry ways continue! Short of good length but not that short to execute a pull but Smith still goes ahead with his shot as he nails it in the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length and on off, Green taps it towards mid on and takes a single.
Length and outside off, Green comes on the front foot and then makes a leave.

Huge appeal but not out says the umpire. No review from the Indians. This one was angled in from outside off, Smith didn't cover the inward movement and shouldered arms. The ball came back in sharply and hit his pad. They appealed but turned down by the umpire.
Outside off, left alone this time.
FOUR! Poor ball and it gets the treatment. Short and on middle and leg. Smith moves inside the crease and thumps it down to the fine leg fence.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Length and on off, played back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a brace. Saini oversteps.
A maiden from Natarajan. Testing over for Green. The last ball is around off on a length, Green gets behind the line of the ball to block.
Angled in from just outside off, Green looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pad again.
Length and on off, watchfully kept out by Green.

NOT OUT! IMPACT IS UMPIRE'S CALL! GREEN SURVIVES AND INDIA DO NOT LOSE A REVIEW! Full and sliding onto middle and leg, Green looks to flick it off the front foot but is beaten to get hit right on the knee roll. Natarajan goes up in appeal so does his teamanates but the umpire is unmoved. Rahane after thinking for a while goes for the revive. Nothing on the HotSpot and RTS. Ball Tracker shows impact umpire's call and wickets too were missing. Green stays on for now.

India take a review for LBW. Fair delivery says the third umpire. Let's see the replays. Doesn't seem to be any bat there. Yes. No bat. Ball Tracker. Impact is umpire's call and missing the wickets too. The onfield call stays.
Length and well going down leg, Green looks to play it to the fine leg area but misses it altogether.
Length and outside off, Green makes a leave first up.
Good length and around middle, clipped wide of the man at mid on for one.
Length and around off, poked towards point.
Full and on the pads, Smith flicks it through mid-wicket for one. Wanted two but decides against it.
Length ball around off, defended.

Play and a miss this time. Lovely from Saini. He is not at his best but beats the outside edge of Smith. Pitches around the shrotish length and around off, it shapes away as Smith looks to defend but is beaten.

FOUR! Slashed! Smith is carrying the form from the first innings. Remember he got out after getting set in the first innings. This one is bowled well wide outside off and on short of good length area. Smith throws the kitchen sink at it to send it off the outside edge over the gully region and into the fence at third man.
Dot to end! It is another tight over from the Indians. Length ball around off, it is tucked towards mid-wicket for nothing.
Length and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fullish and around off, stroked to mid on for nothing.
Banged short and on middle, pulled down to fine leg for one.
Landed around off, pushed towards mid on.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
A maiden from Saini. Top effort from the man who is not 100 percent fit. Shortish and just outside off, pushed on the off side for nothing.
Saini goes little wide outside off, Green lets it be.
Fuller and around off, driven straight to mid off by Green.

FYI - The last time a team chased down a target of 250 runs at Brisbane was way back in 1951 when Australia chased 236 against West Indies. So Australia would look to get past the 250-run mark first and then look for atleast 325 or 350 as the target to set for India to chase.
Around off on a length, pushed towards the cover region.
Shortish and around off, Green looks to defend but the ball takes the outer half and goes to point.
Good length and around off from Saini to begin. Green pushes it back to the bowler.

Navdeep Saini to bowl now. Despite carrying a groin strain he comes onto bowl. How well can he bowl and what if that aggravates it further? But for now he has a task in hand to help India get a wicket or two.
Maiden from Siraj. The last ball is fulish and around off, Smith plays is towards mid off.
Good length and around off, Smith works it towards the leg side.
Back of a length and just outside off, punched well again but straight to the fielder again.
Shortish and just around off, Smith punches it well but finds the cover fielder.
Back of a length and around off and middle, Smith looks to pull but misses to get hit on the body.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Full and on middle, clipped to deep mid-wicket for one.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off for a quick run.
Flatter and around off, turning in. It is tucked down to fine leg for one.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed towards point.

The physio is out there. Agarwal is the one who needs some attention from the physio after he took a blow onto his legs. The physio puts some magic spray on the affected area as Agarwal gulps some painkillers too. He seems to be fine for now to continue.
Ouch! That was swept powerfully. Tossed up and outside off, Smith nails the sweep. However, it hits the leg of the short leg fielder. Mayank is the man there, he looks in pain.
Very full and aroud off, pushed to the right side of the bowler. Sundar fumbles but they don't take run.
Fullish and around off, a solid front foot block from Green.
This time Siraj angles in from off and middle, it is clipped towards square leg.
Slightly fullish and just outside off, Green covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off again, Green lets it be.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Good length and around off, Smith looks to work it on the leg side but gets squared up slightly. The ball goes to point and they take one.
Flatter and on off, punched through covers for a single.
Fuller and on off driven through mid on for a single to get off the mark by Green.
Tossed up on leg, tucked towards mid-wicket.
A full toss on middle, Green pushes it to covers and goes searching for a single as he comes outside his crease but is sent well back in time by Smith there.
Floated on off, pushed to long on for a single.
On off, kept out from within the crease.
Cameron Green comes out to bat now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Strangled down the leg this time! India fighting back again, after a blistering first hour from Australia. Siraj gets his second of the over. A nothing delivery but as far as it fetches a wicket India won't mind. Wade departs without troubling the scorers. Length and down the leg side. Wade shuffles across to off, to tuck it to the leg side but what he could manage is just a faint edge. Which goes at a good height to Pant who dives to his right and takes it just inches above the ground.
On off, kept out.
Length and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Matthew Wade replaces Marnus Labuschagne in the middle.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Siraj deserved that wicket, Nice line, nice length and Labuschagne fails to negotiate. The centurion from the first innings departs this time for 25. Bowls it fast and straight does Siraj as Labuschagne looks to play it off the back foot. The ball is travelling at a good height there as Labuschagne tries to play it away from his body. The ball takes the outside edge and flies to the second slip where Rohit holds onto it. Rahane's move to bring Siraj back into the attack pays off.
FOUR! Deliberately done! Runs are flowing once again. Length and outside off, Labuschagne guides it past the slip and into the third man fence for a boundary.
Shorter and outside off, Labuschagne slashes at it but finds point.
Bowling change! Mohammed Siraj is back on.
Flatter and going down leg as Smith plays the short arm jab straight to the man at square leg. 8 runs off the over.
Floated on leg, clipped towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Over the top! Tossed up on midlde, Labuschagne lofts it over mid on and gets a boundary at long on this time. THE LEAD GOES ON TO 152 RUNS!
Flatter and around off, Labuschagne guides it through short third man and gets a couple by the time the ball is fielded near the ropes.
Tosed up on off, kept out from within the crease.
Full and around middle, Smith clips it to the leg side and takes a quick single on offer.
FOUR! Easy for Labuschagne! A big over for the Aussies. Shardul strays on the pads. Marnus just clips it down to the fine leg fence. 11 off the over.
Shortish and around off, poked towards point.

FOUR! Brilliant effort but Saini fails to prevent the four! Thakur bowls a fuller one on middle, Labuschagne drives it off the front foot through mid on. Saini who is nurturing a groin strain chases the ball till the end. At the first instance it looks like he has saved a certain boundary but the umpires go for a check.
Short and around middle, Labuschagne lets it go through as he ducks.
Another three runs for Smith! Full and angled on the pads, Smith clips it in front of square on the leg side and gets three easily as the fielder in the deep does the mopping up.
Fullish and around off, blocked.
Tossed up ad around off, swept well but straight to square leg.

Smith shows signs of aggression on the first ball. A loopy ball around middle, Smith jumps out of his crease and flicks it over mid-wicket. Saini, struggling with his injury is not the quickest to get to the ball and that allows them to take three. 100 up for the Aussies. The lead now reads 133.
Tossed up and around middle, clipped towards the leg side for a single.
FOUR! Nicely done! Flatter and outside off, Marnus rocks back and manages to guide it through short third man for a boundary.
Shortish and just outside off, cut well but straight to point.
Flatter and around middle, tucked on the leg side.
Labuschagne is off the mark. Fullish and around off, it is tucked towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Wide outside off, left alone again.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Short ball on middle, Labuschagne pulls but finds square leg.
Just outside off on a good length, Labuschagne lets it alone.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Steven Smith is the new man in.

Review time! Warner has been given out LBW. He is walking back. He is sure that this will hit the stumps and he is just walking off. However, Marnus wants him to take the review. And, at the last moment, Warner has asked for it. Let's see if that saves him. No bat and it is three reds on Ball Tracker. Keep walking Warner.

OUT! LBW! One brings two as the saying goes. It has happened here too. THREE REDS! WARNER DEPARTS AND TAKES THE REVIEW TOO! Sundar has been brilliant in this game as he gets a wicket in this innings too. Tosses this one up on off, and gets it to straighten off the surface, Warner tries to play it off the back foot but he fails to get bat on the ball. The ball thuds him on the pads and the appeal from Washington leads the umpire to raise his dreaded finger. Warner initially decides to walk off without reviewing but he is coaxed by Labuschagne to take the review. Just at the last instance before the timer went off he signals 'T'. Replays roll in and there is no spot on the Hot Spot and the RTS fails to pick any nick when the ball is near the bat. Then comes the Ball Tracker and it shows to be three reds as Warner keeps walking off the field.
Flatter and around off, blocked.
On off, pushed to mid on this time by Warner.
Floated around off, Warner drives it a bit uppish through covers and manages a couple this time.
Flatter and on off, Warner punches it to covers.
BEATEN! Tossed up ball around off, Warner lunges forward to defend but is beaten on the outside edge there.
Marnus Labuschagne, the centurion from the first innings, strides out to the middle, replacing Marcus Harris.

DRINKS! A brilliant phase of play from Australia's perspective. Warner and Harris have done well to score briskly. A few edges flew past the fielders too. The Indians gave away a few easy balls too and that allowed the Aussies to get going. Shardul came into the attack and put a slight stop to the scoring rate. He eventually got the wicket of Harris and India will now look to take a couple more as soon as they can. Warner is going along nicely for the Aussies. Interesting phase coming your way.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, India and Thakur get the breakthrough they needed. Thakur is elated and why wouldn't he be? He has been bowling superbly and deserves this wicket. Bowls a short one around middle, Harris sits in response but fails to take his gloves out of the line of the ball. The ball brushes his gloves and goes to the keeper. Pant there accepts the catch gleefully as Thakur appeals to see the umpire raise his finger. A wicket down as Australia are effectively 122/1!
Length ball on the pads, tucked away towards square leg for a single.
Good comeback from Thakur. Bowls another short one but Warner this time drops his wrists and lets the ball sway away from him.
FOUR! Pulled away! Short and around off, Warner is happy as it sits perfectly for him. He pulls it through square leg and fetches yet another boundary.
Length and around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket by Warner off the back foot.
Length ball but down leg, Warner looks to tuck it but fails to get any wood on the ball.
Darted in on middle, Harris drives it to the left of the bowler but fails to beat the man at mid on.
Floated around off, Harris pushes it to covers.
Loopy on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on off, Harris drives it off the leading edge with rolls to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Harris makes a leave this time.
A fuller length ball around off, Warner watchfully blocks it out off the front foot.
Banged in short on middle, Warner sees it and then ducks under it.
Length and just around off, Warner is aware of his stumps as he leaves it alone.
Fuller and around off, Warner strokes it straight to the man at covers.
Another single. Length and around middle, Harris shuffles across a bit before tucking it towards mid-wicket.
Length and around middle, clipped towards fine leg for a single by Warner.
Full and wide outside off, Warner drives it wide of the man at short cover for one.
Tossed up and outside off, driven well but straight to the man at short cover.
Looped up and around off, played to mid on for nothing.
Flatter and around off, blocked.
Fired outside off. Turns away as Warner lets it go.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length and around off, pushed to mid off.
FOUR! Slightly overpitched and Harris nails the drive through mid off. Cracking shot and it races away to the fence.
Just outside off on a length, kept out.
Shortish and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
Very full and outside off, digged towards point for one.
Beaten again! Terrific stuff from Shardul. A fullish ball just outside off, Warner looks to drive but fails to make any connection.
Shortish and outside off, left alone.
Full and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Darted outside off again, Harris lets it be.
Outside off, left alone this time.
Full and around off, blocked.
Full and around off, driven to deep cover for a single.
Shortish and around off, kept out.
Good length and around off, defended solidly.
Length ball around off, punched through the covers for a brace.
Outside off, left alone.
Fullish and just outside off, poked towards point for one.
Beaten! Another jaffa from Shardul. Just around off and middle, Warner looks to block but it comes back in a touch and beats the outside edge of Warner.
Loopy and around off, blocked.
FOUR! Nicely done! Shortish and just outside off, Harris moves on his back foot and then guides it through short third man for a boundary. Fine shot.
Outside off, left alone.
Short and wide outside off, cuts but finds point.
Full ball on middle, it is flicked through mid-wicket. Saini gives it a chase. Three taken before he can return the ball to the keeper. THE LEAD NOW STANDS AT 101 RUNS!
Darted outside off, left alone.
Jaffa to end! Fullish and just outside off, Harris looks to force the drive on the off side but is beaten. A maiden from Shardul.
Shortish and just outside off, poked towards the gully region.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Another one outside off, Harris is not interested as he watches it go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball around off, defended towards mid off.
Change of ends for Shardul Thakur. 1-0-1-0 so far from him.
Flatter and around off, kept out by Warner.
Full and just outside off, stroked to deep cover for one.
Looped up and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Play and a miss! Tossed up and outside off, Harris reaches out and looks to go over covers but misses as the ball turns away.
Very full ball on middle, Warner flicks it wide of the man at mid on for one.
Washington Sundar to bowl now. 1-0-3-0 from him so far.
Around off on a length, Harris keeps it out towards mid off.
Full and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
In the channel outside off, Harris lets it be.
Good length and just outside off, poked towards point.
Length ball around off, defended solidly.

Dot to end the over! Short ball on middle, Harris looks to take him on but mistimes the pull towards the left of the bowler.
Length and around off, Harris defends it watchfully.
Another one outside off from Shardul. Harris lets it go to the keeper.
Full and wide outside off, Harris lets it be.
Banged short and on middle, kept out.

In the channel outside off, Harris lets it go this time. 8 off the over.
FOUR! Superb! Lovely shot! Fuller and around off, Harris leans into the drive and creams it through covers for another boundary.
Fuller and angled across off, Harris watches the ball and then lifts his willow to allow a safe passage for the ball to settle into the mitts of the keeper.
Length and on middle and leg, Harris tucks it to the leg side this time.
Fuller and wider of off stump, Harris reaches out to it and plays it to the off side this time.
FOUR! Punched! Short of a good length angled across off, Harris stands tall and then punches it through covers for a boundary. Runs starting to flow freely for Australia.
Length and in that channel outside off, Warner has nothing doing with it as he leaves it. 14 off the over. A good one for Australia.
Fuller and around off, Warner is well forward as he plays the defensive stroke.
Slightly back of a length ball around off, Harris taps it towards cover-point and crosses over for a single.

FOUR BYES! More runs for Australia. A length ball down the leg side. Harris looks to flick again but he misses. Pant dives to his right, gets a glove to it but fails to collect. And it races away to the fence.
FOUR! Flicked! Fullish ball on the pads, Harris flicks it through square leg and finds the fence. Natarajan oversteps too.

Fullish and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Short and around off, swatted straight to mid on.

Full and down the leg side. Harris looks to flick but misses. Pant does well to move to his right to collect the ball.

Another leave as Siraj bowls this one slightly fuller but outside off.
Length ball just outside off, Warner covers his stumps and makes a leave.
